  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Preamble'
      title: Preamble
      number: 1
      content: 'These are the words that Moses spoke to all of Israel on the other
        side of the Jordan in the desert, in the desert plateau opposite Suph, between
        Paran and between Tophel and Laban and Hazeroth and Dizahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It is a journey of eleven days from Herob by the way of Mount Seir
        up to Kadesh Barnea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And it was in the fortieth year, on the eleventh month, on the first
        day of the month, Moses spoke to the Israelites according to all that Yahweh
        had instructed him to speak to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'This happened after defeating Sihon king of the Amorites, who was
        reigning in Heshbon, and Og the king of Bashan, who was reigning in Ashtaroth
        in Edrei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Historical Prologue'
      title: Historical Prologue
      number: 5
      content: 'On the other side of  the Jordan in the land of Moab Moses began
        to explain this law, saying:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CYahweh our God spoke to us at Horeb, saying, \u2018You have
        stayed long enough at this mountain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Turn now and move on, and go into the hill of the Amorites and to
        all of the neighboring regions in the Jordan Valley in the hill country and
        in the Negev and in the coastal area along the sea, into the land of the
        Canaanites and into the Lebanon, as far as the great river Euphrates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Look, I have set the land before you; go and take possession of the
        land that Yahweh swore to your ancestors, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob,
        to give it to them and to their offspring after them.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd I spoke to them at that time, saying, \u2018I am not able
        to bear you alone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Yahweh your God has multiplied you, and look; you are today as the
        stars of the heaven in number.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yahweh, the God of your ancestors, may he add to you as you are now
        a thousand times, and may he bless you just as he promised you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'How can I bear you by myself, your burden and your load and your
        strife? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Choose for yourselves wise and discerning and knowledgeable men for
        each of your tribes, and I will appoint them as your leaders.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CAnd you answered me, and you said, \u2018The thing you have
        said to do is good.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And so I took the leaders of your tribes, wise and knowledgeable
        men, and then I appointed them as leaders over you as commanders of groups
        of thousands and commanders of groups of hundreds and commanders of groups
        of fifties and commanders of groups of tens as officials for your tribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And at that time I instructed your judges, saying, \u2018hear out
        your fellow men, and then judge fairly between a man and between his brother
        and between his opponent who is a resident alien.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "You must not be partial in your judgment;  hear out the small person
        as also the great person; do not be intimidated by any person, because the
        judgment is God\u2019s; and the case that is too difficult for you, bring
        it to me, and I will hear it out.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And so I instructed you at that time concerning all of the things
        that you should do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThen we set out from Horeb, and we went through the whole of
        that great and terrible desert that you saw on the way to the hill country
        of the Amorites as Yahweh our God had commanded us, and so we came up to
        Kadesh Barnea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "I said to you, \u2018You have reached the hill country of the Amorites
        that Yahweh our God is giving to us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "See, Yahweh your God has set before you the land; go up and possess
        it as Yahweh the God of your ancestors said to you; do not fear and do not
        be dismayed.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThen all of you approached me, and you said, \u2018Let us send
        men before us, and let them explore the land for us, and let them bring back
        a report to us concerning the way that we should take and concerning the
        cities that we shall come to.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The plan was good in my opinion, and so I took from among you twelve
        men, one from each tribe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And they set out and went up into the hill country, and they went
        up to the wadi of Eschol, and they spied out the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "They took in their hands some of the fruit of the land, and they
        brought it down to us, and they brought to us back a report, and they said,
        \u2018The land that Yahweh our God is giving to us is good.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But you were not willing to go up, and you rebelled against the command
        of Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And you grumbled in your tents, and you said, \u2018Because of the
        hatred of Yahweh toward us he has brought us out from the land of Egypt to
        give us into the hand of the Amorites to destroy us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Where can we go up? Our brothers have made our hearts melt, saying,
        \u201CThe people are greater and taller than we are, and there are great
        fortified cities reaching up to heaven, and we saw the sons of the Anakites
        living there.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CAnd so I said to you, \u2018Do not be terrified, and do not
        fear them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Yahweh your God, who is going before you, will himself fight for
        you, just as he did for you in Egypt before your eyes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "and just as he did in the wilderness when you saw that Yahweh your
        God carried you, just as someone carries his son, all along the way that
        you traveled until you reached this place.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'But through all of this you did not trust in Yahweh your God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'who goes before you on your way, seeking a place for your encampment,
        in fire at night and in a cloud by day, to show you the way that you should
        go.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CThen Yahweh heard the sound of your words, and he was angry,
        and he swore, saying,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u2018No one of these men of this evil generation will see the good
        land that I swore to give to your ancestors,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "except Caleb, the son of Jephunneh; he himself shall see it, and
        to him I will give the land upon which he has trodden and to his sons because
        he followed Yahweh unreservedly.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Even with me Yahweh was angry because of you, saying, \u2018Not even
        you shall enter there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Joshua, the son of Nun, your assistant, will go there; encourage
        him because he will cause Israel to inherit it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And your little children, who you thought shall become plunder, and
        your sons, who do not today know good or bad, shall themselves go there,
        and I will give it to them, and they shall take possession of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But you turn and set out in the direction of the wilderness by way
        of the Red Sea.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CYou replied and said to me, \u2018We have sinned against Yahweh,
        and now we will go up and fight according to all that Yahweh our God commanded
        us\u2019; and so each man fastened on his battle gear, and you regarded it
        as easy to go up into the hill country. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "So Yahweh said to me, \u2018Say to them, \u201CYou shall not go up,
        and you shall not fight because I am not in your midst; you will be defeated
        before your enemies.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So I spoke to you, but you did not listen; you rebelled against the
        command of Yahweh; you behaved presumptuously, and you went up into the hill
        country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'The Amorites living in the hill country went out to oppose you and
        chased you as a swarm of wild honey bees do; and so they beat you down in
        Seir as far as Hormah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'So you returned and wept before Yahweh; but Yahweh did not listen
        to your voice and did not pay any attention to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'You stayed in Kadesh many days; such were the days that you stayed
        there. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CThen we turned and set out toward the wilderness in the direction
        of the Red Sea, as Yahweh told me, and we went around Mount Seir for many
        days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Yahweh spoke to me, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018Long enough you have been skirting this mountain; turn yourselves
        north, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and instruct the people, saying, \u201CYou are about to cross through
        the territory of your brothers, the descendants of Esau, who are living in
        Seir; they will be afraid of you, and so be very careful. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Do not get involved in battle with them, for I will not give you
        any of their land, not even a foot\u2019s breadth of it; since I have given
        Mount Seir as a possession for Esau. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall buy food from them so that you may eat; and also you shall
        purchase water from them with money so that you may drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The fact of the matter is, Yahweh your God has blessed you in all
        the work you have done; he knows your travels with respect to this great
        wilderness; forty years Yahweh your God has been with you; you have not lacked
        a thing.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And so we passed by our brothers, the descendants of Esau, who live
        in Seir, past the road of the Arabah, from Elath and Ezion Geber, and we
        turned and traveled along the route of the desert of Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Yahweh said to me, \u2018You shall not attack Moab, and you shall
        not engage in war with them, for I will not give you any of his land as a
        possession; I have given Ar to the descendants of Lot as a possession.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '(The Emim previously lived in it, a people large, numerous, and tall,
        like the Anakites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They were reckoned also as Rephaim as the Anakites were; but the
        Moabites called them Emim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Horites previously lived in Seir, but the descendants of Esau
        dispossessed them and destroyed them from among themselves, as Israel did
        with respect to the land of their possession that Yahweh gave to them.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So now arise and cross over the wadi of Zered yourselves; and so
        we crossed the wadi of Zered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now the length of time that we had traveled from Kadesh Barnea until
        the time when we crossed the wadi of Zered was thirty-eight years, until
        the perishing of all of that generation; that is, the men of war from the
        midst of the camp as Yahweh had sworn to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The hand of Yahweh was against them to root them out from the midst
        of the camp until they perished completely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAnd then when all the men of war had died from among the people, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Yahweh spoke to me, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018You are about to cross over the boundary of Moab today at Ar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When you approach the border of the Ammonites, you shall not harass
        them, and you shall not get involved in battle with them, for I have not
        given the land of the Ammonites to you as a possession; because I have given
        it to the descendants of Lot as a possession. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '(It is also considered the land of Rephaim; Rephaim lived in it previously,
        and the Ammonites called them Zamzummim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'a people great and numerous and as tall as the Anakites; Yahweh destroyed
        them from before them, and they dispossessed them and settled in place of
        them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'just as he did for the descendants of Esau, who live in Seir, when
        he destroyed the Horites from before them and dispossessed them, and then
        they settled in their place up to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And also the Avvites, who lived in villages as far as Gaza, and the
        Caphtorim, who came out from Caphtor, destroyed them and then settled in
        their place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Arise, set out and cross over the wadi of Arnon. Look! I have given
        Sihon the Amorite, the king of Heshbon, and his land into your hand; begin
        to take possession of it, and engage with him in battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "This day I will begin to place the dread of you and the fear of you
        before the peoples under all the heavens. They will hear the report about
        you, and so they will shake and tremble because of you.\u2019   "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CSo I sent messengers from the wilderness of Kedemoth to Sihon
        king of Heshbon; I sent terms of peace, saying,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u2018Let me cross through your land and only along the road I will
        go; I will not turn aside to the right or to the left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Food for money you shall sell me, so that I may eat, and water for
        money you will give to me, so that I may drink; just let me cross on foot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Just as the descendants of Esau did for me, who live in Seir, and
        the Moabites, who live in Ar, until I cross the Jordan into the land that
        Yahweh our God is giving to us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But Sihon king of Heshbon was not willing to let us cross through
        his territory because Yahweh your God hardened his spirit and made him obstinate
        in order to give him into your hand, just as he has now done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Yahweh said to me, \u2018Look! I have begun to give over to you Sihon
        and his land; begin to take possession of his land.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then Sihon and all his people came out to meet us for battle at Jahaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And so Yahweh our God gave him over to us, and we struck him down,
        and his sons and all of his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So we captured all of his cities at that time, and we destroyed each
        town of males and the women and the children; we did not leave behind a survivor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'We took only the livestock as spoil for ourselves, and also the booty
        of the cities that we had captured. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'From Aroer, which is on the edge of the wadi of Arnon and the city
        that was in the wadi on up to Gilead, there was not a city that was inaccessible
        to us; Yahweh our God gave everything to us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Only the land of the Ammonites you did not approach, all along the
        whole upper region of the Jabbok River and the towns of the hill country,
        according to all that Yahweh our God had instructed. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CThen we turned, and we went up the road to Bashan, and Og
        the king of Bashan came out to meet us, he and all of his army for the battle
        at Edrei. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Yahweh said to me, \u2018You should not fear him, for I have
        given him and all of his army and his land into your hand. And so you will
        do to him as you did to Sihon the king of the Amorites, who was reigning
        in Heshbon.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And so Yahweh our God also gave Og the king of Bashan, and all of
        his army into our hand, and we struck him down until not a survivor remained
        to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And we captured all of his towns at that time; there was not a city
        that we did not take from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All of these were fortified towns with high walls, gates, and bars,
        apart from very many of the villages of the open country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And so we destroyed them just as we had done to Sihon the king of
        Heshbon; we destroyed utterly each town of males, the women, and the little
        children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But all of the livestock and the booty of the towns we kept as spoil
        for ourselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAnd so we took at that time the land from the control of the
        two kings of the Amorites who were on the other side of the Jordan, from
        the wadi of Arnon up to Mount Hermon.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "(The Sidonians called Hermon \u2018Sirion,\u2019 and the Amorites
        called it \u2018Senir.\u2019) "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'All of the towns of the plateau and the whole of Gilead and all of
        Bashan up to Salecah and Edrei, the towns of the kingdom of Og in Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "(For only Og, king of Bashan, was left from the remnant of the Rephaim.
        Indeed, his bedstead\u2014it was a bedstead of iron. It is in Rabbah of the
        Ammonites. Nine cubits is its length, and four cubits is its width according
        to the cubit of a man.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And so we took possession of this land at that time, from Aroer,
        which is on the edge of the wadi of Arnon, and also half of the hill country
        of Gilead and its towns I gave to the Reubenites and to the Gadites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the remainder of Gilead and all of Bashan, the kingdom of Og,
        I gave to the half-tribe of Manasseh, the whole region of Argo. All of that
        area of Bashan was called the land of the Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Jair the descendant of Manasseh acquired the whole region of Argob,
        up to the boundary of the Geshurites and the Maacathites, and he called it,
        that is Bashan, after his own name, Havvoth Jair, as it still is today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And also I gave Gilead to Makir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And to the Reubenites and to the Gadites I gave, from Gilead up to
        the wadi of Arnon, the middle of the wadi as a boundary and up to the Jabbok
        River, the boundary of the Ammonites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the Jordan Valley with the Jordan River as its boundary, from
        Kinnereth up to the Sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea, with the slopes of Pisgah
        toward the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAnd I charged you all at that time when I said, \u201CYahweh
        has given you\u2014to all of you\u2014this land to possess. All the warriors
        shall cross over, ready to fight, before your brothers, the Israelites.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Only your wives and your little children and your livestock (I know
        that you have much livestock) must stay in your towns that I have given you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'until Yahweh shall give rest to your brothers as he did to you, and
        also they take possession of the land that Yahweh your God is giving to them
        beyond the Jordan; then they may return, each one to his possession that
        I have given to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And I commanded Joshua at that time, saying, \u2018Your eyes see
        all that Yahweh your God has done to these two kings; so Yahweh will do to
        all of the kingdoms where you are about to cross over to. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You shall not fear them, for Yahweh your God is the one fighting
        for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAnd I pleaded with Yahweh at that time, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018Lord Yahweh, you have begun to show your servant your greatness
        and your strong hand, for what god is there in the heaven or on the earth
        who can do according to your works and according to your mighty deeds? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Let me cross over, please, and let me see the good land that is beyond
        the Jordan, this good hill country and Lebanon.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Yahweh was very angry with me because of you, and he would not
        listen to me, and Yahweh said, \u2018Enough of that from you! You shall not
        speak to me any longer about this matter! "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Go up to the top of Pisgah and look around you toward the west, toward
        the north, and toward the east, and view the land with your eyes, for you
        will not cross this Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now instruct Joshua and support him and encourage him because he
        himself will cross over before this people and enable them to inherit the
        land that you will see.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So we remained in the valley opposite Beth Peor. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Introduction to the Stipulations'
      title: Introduction to the Stipulations
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CNow, Israel, listen to the rules and to the regulations that
        I am teaching you to do, in order that you may live and you may go in and
        you may take possession of the land that Yahweh, the God of your ancestors,
        is giving to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You must not add to the word that I am commanding you, and you shall
        not take away from it in order to keep the commands of Yahweh your God that
        I am commanding you to observe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Your eyes have seen what Yahweh did with the case of Baal Peor, for
        each man that followed after Baal Peor Yahweh your God destroyed from your
        midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But you, the ones holding fast to Yahweh your God, are all alive
        today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'See, I now teach you rules and regulations just as Yahweh my God
        has commanded me, to observe them just so in the midst of the land where
        you are going, to take possession of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And you must observe them diligently, for that is your wisdom and
        your insight before the eyes of the people, who will hear all of these rules,
        and they will say, \u2018Surely this great nation is a wise and discerning
        people.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For what great nation has for it a god near to it as Yahweh our God,
        whenever we call upon him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And what other great nation has for it just rules and regulations
        just like this whole law that I am setting before you today?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CHowever, take care for yourself and watch your inner self closely,
        so that you do not forget the things that your eyes have seen, so that they
        do not slip from your mind all the days of your life; and you shall make
        them known to your children and to your grandchildren.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Remember the day that you stood before Yahweh your God at Horeb when
        Yahweh said to me, \u2018Summon for me the people so that I can tell them
        my words, that they may learn to fear me all of the days they are alive on
        the earth and so that they may teach their children.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And so you came near, and you stood under the mountain, and the mountain
        was burning with fire up to the heart of the heaven, dark with a very thick
        cloud.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Yahweh spoke to you from the midst of the fire; you heard a sound
        of words, but you did not see a form\u2014only a voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he declared to you his covenant, the Ten Commandments, which
        he charged you to observe, and he wrote them on the two tablets of stone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Yahweh charged me at that time to teach you rules and regulations
        for your observation of them in the land that you are about to cross into
        to take possession of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CSo you must be very careful for yourselves, because you did
        not see any form on the day Yahweh spoke to you at Horeb from the midst of
        the fire, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'so that you do not ruin yourselves and make for yourselves a divine
        image in a form of any image, a replica of male or female, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'a replica of any animal that is upon the earth, a replica of any
        winged bird that flies in the air, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'a replica of any creeping thing on the ground, a replica of any fish
        that is in the water below the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And do this so that you do not lift your eyes toward heaven and observe
        the sun and the moon and the stars, all the host of the heaven, and be led
        astray and bow down to them and serve them, things that Yahweh your God has
        allotted to all of the peoples under all of the heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But Yahweh has taken you and brought you out from the furnace of
        iron, from Egypt, to be a people of inheritance to him, as it is this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CAnd Yahweh was angry with me because of you, and he swore that
        I would not cross the Jordan and that I would not go to the good land that
        Yahweh your God is giving you as an inheritance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For I am going to die in this land; I am not going to cross the Jordan,
        but you are going to cross, and you are going to take possession of this
        good land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Watch out for yourselves so that you do not forget the covenant of
        Yahweh your God that he had made with you and make for yourselves a divine
        image of the form of anything that Yahweh your God has forbidden,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'for Yahweh your God is a devouring fire, a jealous God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CWhen you have had children and grandchildren and you have grown
        old in the land and you act corruptly and you make a divine image of the
        form of anything and you do evil in the eyes of Yahweh your God, thus provoking
        him to anger, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I call to witness against you today the heaven and the earth, that
        you will perish soon and completely from the land that you are crossing the
        Jordan into it to take possession of it; you will not live long on it, but
        you will be completely destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Yahweh will scatter you among the peoples, and you will be left
        few in number among the nations to where Yahweh will lead you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And you will there serve gods made by human hands, of wood and stone,
        gods that cannot see and cannot hear and cannot eat and cannot smell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'But from there you shall seek Yahweh your God and will find him,
        if you seek him with all your heart and with all your soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'In your distress when all these things have found you in the latter
        days, then you will return to Yahweh your God, and you will listen to his
        voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For Yahweh your God is a compassionate God; he will not abandon you,
        and he will not destroy you, and he will not forget the covenant of your
        ancestors that he swore to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CYes, ask, please, about former days that preceded you from
        the day that God created humankind on the earth; ask even from one end of
        the heaven up to the other end of heaven whether anything ever happened like
        this great thing or whether anything like it was ever heard.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Has a people ever heard the voice of God speaking from the midst
        of the fire, just as you heard it, and lived? '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Or has a god ever attempted to go to take for himself a nation from
        the midst of a nation, using trials and signs and wonders and war, with an
        outstretched arm and with great and awesome deeds, like all that Yahweh your
        God did for you in Egypt before your eyes? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'You yourselves were shown this wonder in order for you to acknowledge
        that Yahweh is the God; there is no other God besides him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'From heaven he made you hear his voice to teach you, and on the earth
        he showed you his great fire, and you heard his words from the midst of the
        fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And because he loved your ancestors he chose their descendants after
        them. And he brought you forth from Egypt with his own presence, by his great
        strength, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'to drive out nations greater and more numerous than you from before
        you, to bring you and to give to you their land as an inheritance, as it
        is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So you shall acknowledge today, and you must call to mind that Yahweh
        is God in heaven above and on the earth beneath. There is no other God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And you shall keep his rules and his commandments that I am commanding
        you today, so that it may go well for you and for your children after you,
        and so that you may remain a long time on the land that Yahweh your God is
        giving to you during all of those days.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then Moses set apart three cities on the other side of the Jordan,
        toward the east,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'in order for a manslayer to flee there who has killed his neighbor
        without intent and was not hating him previously, and so he could flee to
        one of these cities and be safe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'He set apart Bezer in the wilderness in the land of the plateau of
        the Reubenites; Ramoth in Gilead of the Gadites, and Golan in Bashan of the
        Manassites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Now this is the law that Moses set before the Israelites;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'these are the legal provisions and the rules and the regulations
        that Moses spoke to the Israelites when they left Egypt,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'beyond the Jordan in the valley opposite Beth Peor in the land of
        Sihon the king of the Amorites, who was reigning in Heshbon and whom Moses
        and the Israelites defeated when they came out of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And so they took possession of his land and the land of Og king of
        Bashan, the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan, eastward,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'from Aroer, which is on the bank of the wadi of Arnon and as far
        as Mount Sirion; that is, Hermon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'and all of the Arabah beyond the Jordan, eastward, and as far as
        the Sea of the Arabah under the slopes of Pisgah. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Basic Stipulations'
      title: Basic Stipulations
      number: 1
      content: "And then Moses summoned all of Israel and said to them, \u201CHear,
        Israel, the rules and the regulations that I am speaking in your ears today,
        and you shall learn them, and you must observe them diligently.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Yahweh our God made a covenant with us at Horeb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It was not with our ancestors that Yahweh made this covenant, but
        with these of us who are here alive today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Face to face Yahweh spoke with you at the mountain from the midst
        of the fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I was standing between Yahweh and you at that time to report to you
        the word of Yahweh, for you were afraid because of the presence of the fire,
        and so you did not go up the mountain. He said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018I am Yahweh your God, who brought you out from the land of
        Egypt, from the house of slavery. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'There shall not be for you other gods besides me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u2018You shall not make for yourself a divine image of any type
        of form that is in the heaven above or that is on the earth beneath or that
        is in the water under the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u2018You shall not bow down to them, and you shall not serve them,
        for I, Yahweh your God, am a jealous God, punishing the guilt of fathers
        upon their children and upon the third and upon the fourth generation of
        those hating me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but showing loyal love to thousands of those who love me and of those
        who keep my commandments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u2018You shall not take up the name of Yahweh your God for a worthless
        purpose, for Yahweh will not leave unpunished anyone who uses his name for
        a worthless purpose. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u2018Observe the Sabbath day to make it holy, just as Yahweh your
        God has commanded you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Six days you shall work, and you shall do all of your work, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but the seventh day is a Sabbath unto Yahweh your God; you shall
        not do any work, or your son, or your daughter, or your slave, or your slave
        woman, or your ox, or your donkey, or any of your domestic animals, or your
        resident alien who is in your towns, so that your slave and your slave woman
        may rest as you rest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And you shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt,
        and Yahweh your God brought you out with a strong hand and with an outstretched
        arm; therefore, Yahweh your God commanded you to keep the Sabbath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018Honor your father and your mother, as Yahweh your God commanded
        you, so that it will be good for you in the land that Yahweh your God is
        giving to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018You shall not murder. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018And you shall not commit adultery. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u2018And you shall not steal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u2018And you shall not falsely bear evidence against your neighbor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u2018And you shall not covet the wife of your neighbor, and you
        shall not crave the house of your neighbor, his field or his slave or his
        slave woman or his ox and his donkey or anything that belongs to your neighbor.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThese words Yahweh spoke to your whole assembly at the mountain
        from the midst of the fire and the very thick cloud with a loud voice, and
        he did not add anything, and then he wrote them on two tablets of stone and
        gave them to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And then when you heard the voice from the midst of the darkness,
        and as the mountain was burning with fire, and and all the heads of your
        tribes and your elders approached me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "you said, \u2018Look, Yahweh our God has shown us his glory and his
        greatness, and we have heard his voice from the midst of the fire; this day
        we have seen that God can speak with a human being, yet he remains alive.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And so then why shall we die, for this great fire will consume us
        if we continue to hear the voice of Yahweh our God any longer, and so we
        shall die? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For who is there of all flesh who has heard the voice of the living
        God speaking from the midst of the fire as we have heard it and remained
        alive?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "You go near and hear everything that Yahweh our God will say; and
        then you tell us all that Yahweh our God tells you, and we will listen, and
        we will do it.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CAnd Yahweh heard the sound of your words when you spoke to
        me, and Yahweh said to me, \u2018I have heard the sound of the words of this
        people that they have spoken to you; they are right with respect to all that
        they have spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "If only they had such a mind\u2019; that is, to fear me and to keep
        all my commandments at all times, so that it will go well for them and for
        their children forever.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Go! Say to them, \u201CReturn to your tents.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But you stand here with me, and let me tell you all of the commandments
        and the rules and the regulations that you shall teach them, so that they
        may do them in the land that I am giving to them to take possession of it.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CSo you must be careful to do just as Yahweh your God commanded
        you; you shall not turn to the right or to the left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "In exactly the path that Yahweh your God has commanded, you must
        go, so that you may live and it will go well for you and you may live long
        in the land that you will take possession of.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Detailed Stipulations'
      title: Detailed Stipulations
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CNow this is the commandment, the rules and the regulations,
        that Yahweh your God charged to teach to you for you to observe in the land
        that you are about to cross over into to take possession of it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'so that you may revere Yahweh your God by keeping all his statutes
        and his commandments that I am commanding you, you and your children and
        grandchildren, all the days of your life and so you may live long lives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And you shall hear, Israel, and be careful to observe these instructions,
        so that it may go well for you and that you may multiply greatly, just as
        Yahweh, the God of your ancestors, promised you, in a land with milk and
        honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CHear, Israel, Yahweh our God, Yahweh is unique.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And you shall love Yahweh your God with all of your heart and with
        all of your soul and with all of your might. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And these words that I am commanding you today shall be on your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And you shall recite them to your children, and you shall talk about
        them at the time of your living in your house and at the time of your going
        on the road and at the time of your lying down and at the time of your rising
        up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And you shall bind them as a sign on your hand, and they shall be
        as an emblem between your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And you shall write them on the doorframe of your house and on your
        gates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd then it will happen that when Yahweh your God will bring
        you to the land that he swore to your ancestors, to Abraham, to Isaac, and
        to Jacob, to give to you large and fine cities that you did not build, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and houses full of all sorts of good things that you did not fill,
        and hewn cisterns that you did not hew, vineyards and olive groves that you
        did not plant, and you have eaten your fill,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then take care for yourself, so that you do not forget Yahweh, who
        brought you out from the land of Egypt from the house of slavery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CYou shall fear Yahweh your God, and you shall serve him, and
        by his name you shall swear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall not go after other gods from the gods of the peoples who
        are all around you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'for Yahweh your God is a jealous god in your midst, so that the anger
        of Yahweh your God would be kindled, and he would destroy you from the face
        of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You shall not put Yahweh your God to the test, as you tested him
        at Massah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You shall diligently keep the commandments of Yahweh your God and
        his legal provisions and his rules that he has commanded you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And you shall do what is right and good in the eyes of Yahweh, so
        that it shall go well for you and so that you may go and you may take possession
        of the good land that Yahweh swore for your ancestors,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'by driving out all of your enemies before you, just as Yahweh has
        promised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CWhen your child asks you in the future, saying, \u2018What
        is the meaning of the legal provisions and the rules and the regulations
        that Yahweh our God commanded for you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then you shall say to your child, \u2018We were slaves of Pharaoh
        in Egypt, and Yahweh brought us out from Egypt with a strong hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Yahweh gave great and awesome signs and wonders in Egypt against
        Pharaoh and against his entire household in our presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But he brought us out from there in order to bring us here to give
        us the land that he swore to our ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And so Yahweh commanded us to observe all of these rules and to revere
        Yahweh our God for our benefit all the days that we live, as it is today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And it shall be righteousness for us if we diligently observe and
        do all of this commandment before Yahweh our God, as he has commanded us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CWhen Yahweh your God brings you into the land that you are
        about to enter into it to take possession of it, and he drives out many nations
        before you, the Hittites and the Girgashites and the Amorites and the Canaanites
        and the Hivites and the Jebusites, seven nations mightier and more numerous
        than you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and Yahweh your God will give them over to you and you defeat them,
        you must utterly destroy them; you shall not make a covenant with them, and
        you shall not show mercy to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And you shall not intermarry with them; you shall not give your daughter
        to their son; and you shall not take his daughter for your son.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For their sons and daughters will cause your son to turn away from
        following me, and so they will serve other gods, and the anger of Yahweh
        would be kindled against you, and he would quickly destroy you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But this is what you must do to them: you shall break down their
        altars, and their stone pillars you shall smash, and their Asherah poles
        you shall hew down, and you shall burn their idols with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For you are a holy people for Yahweh your God; Yahweh your God has
        chosen you to be for him a people, a treasured possession from among all
        the peoples that are on the face of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYahweh loved you and chose you not because of your great number
        exceeding all other peoples, for you are fewer than all of the peoples, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'but because of the love of Yahweh for you and because of his keeping
        of the sworn oath that he swore to your ancestors, Yahweh brought you out
        with a strong hand and redeemed you from the house of slavery, from the hand
        of Pharaoh, the king of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So know that Yahweh your God, he is God, the trustworthy God, maintaining
        his covenant and his loyal love with those who love him and with those who
        keep his commandments to a thousand generations,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but repaying those who hate him in their own person to destroy them;
        he is not slow with those who hate him in their own person; he repays them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And so you shall keep the commandment and the rules and the regulations
        that I am commanding you today to observe them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd then because you listen to these regulations and you diligently
        keep and you do them, then Yahweh your God will maintain his covenant and
        his loyal love that he swore to your ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he will love you, and he will bless you, and he will multiply
        you, and he will bless the fruit of your womb and the fruit of your soil,
        your grain, your wine, and your olive oil, and newborn calves of your cattle,
        and the newborn lambs of your flocks in the land that he swore to your ancestors
        to give you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall be blessed more than all of the peoples; among you there
        shall not be sterility and bareness, even among domestic animals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Yahweh will turn away from you all the illness and all the harmful
        diseases of Egypt that you experienced; he will not lay them on you, but
        he will lay them on all of those who hate you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And you shall devour all of the peoples that Yahweh your God is giving
        to you; you shall not pity them, and you shall not serve their gods, which
        will be a snare for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CIf you think in your heart, \u2018These nations are more numerous
        than I, so how can I dispossess them?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'then remember you must not be afraid of them; you must well remember
        what Yahweh your God did to Pharaoh and to all of Egypt: '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the great trials that your eyes saw and the signs and the wonders
        and the workings of the strong hand and the outstretched arm by which Yahweh
        your God brought you out; so Yahweh your God will do to all of the peoples
        because of whom you are in fear before them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And, moreover, Yahweh your God will send the hornets among them until
        both the survivors and the fugitives are destroyed before you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You must not be in dread from the presence of them, because Yahweh
        your God, who is in your midst, is a great and awesome God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Yahweh your God will clear away these nations from before you
        little by little; you will not be able to finish them off quickly, lest the
        wild animals multiply against you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But Yahweh your God will give them to you, and he will throw them
        into great panic until they are destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And he will give their kings into your hand, and you shall blot out
        their names from under the heaven; anyone will not be able to stand against
        you until you destroy them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You shall burn the images of their gods with fire; you shall not
        covet the silver or gold that is on them, and so you take it for yourself,
        so that you are not ensnared by it, for it is a detestable thing to Yahweh
        your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And you must not bring a detestable thing into your house, or you
        will become a thing devoted to destruction like it; you must utterly detest
        it, and you must utterly abhor it, for it is an object devoted to destruction. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CAll of the commandments that I am commanding you today you
        must diligently observe, so that you may live and multiply, and you may go
        and take possession of the land that Yahweh swore to your ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And you shall remember all of the way that Yahweh your God led you
        during these forty years in the desert in order to humble you and to test
        you to know what is in your heart, whether you would diligently keep his
        commandments or not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he humbled you and let you go hungry, and then he fed you with
        that which you did not know nor did your ancestors know, in order to make
        you know that not by bread alone but by all that goes out of the mouth of
        Yahweh humankind shall live. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Your clothing did not wear out on you, and your feet did not swell
        during these forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And you should know with your heart that as a man disciplines his
        son, so Yahweh your God is disciplining you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So you must keep the commandments of Yahweh your God by walking in
        his ways and by fearing him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For Yahweh your God is bringing you to a good land with streams of
        water, springs and underground water, welling up in the valleys and in the
        hills,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'to a land of wheat and barley and vines and fig trees and pomegranate
        trees, a land of olive trees, olive oil and honey; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'to a land where you may eat food in it without scarcity; you will
        not find anything lacking in it, a land where its stones are iron and from
        its mountains you can mine copper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And you will eat, and you will be satisfied, and you will bless Yahweh
        your God because of the good land that he has given to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CTake care for yourself so that you not forget Yahweh your God
        by not keeping his commandments and his regulations and his statutes that
        I am commanding you today,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'lest when you have eaten and you are satisfied and you have built
        good houses and you live in them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and your herds and your flocks have multiplied, and you have accumulated
        silver and gold, and all that you have has multiplied, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'then your heart becomes proud and you forget Yahweh your God, the
        one who brought you out from the land of Egypt, from the house of slavery, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the one leading you in the great and terrible desert infested with
        dangerous snakes and scorpions and parched ground, where there is no water,
        and the one bringing out water for you from flint rock, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the one feeding you manna in the desert, food that your ancestors
        did not know, in order to humble you and in order to test you so that he
        could do good to you in the future.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And you may think in your heart, \u2018My strength and the might
        of my hand acquired this wealth for me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But you must remember Yahweh your God, for he is the one giving you
        strength to acquire wealth in order to confirm his covenant that he swore
        to your ancestors as it is today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And it will happen that if you indeed forget Yahweh your God and
        you go after other gods and you serve them and you bow down before them,
        I warn you today that you will surely perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As with the nations that Yahweh is destroying before you, so you
        shall perish because you would not obey the voice of Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CHear, Israel, you are about to cross the Jordan today to go
        to dispossess nations larger and more numerous than you, great cities fortified
        with high walls,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "a great and tall people, the sons of the Anakites, whom you know
        and of whom you have heard it said, \u2018Who could stand before the sons
        of Anak?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You should know today that Yahweh your God is the one crossing ahead
        of you as a devouring fire; he will destroy them, and he will subdue them
        before you; so you will dispossess them, and you will destroy them quickly,
        just as Yahweh promised you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYou shall not say to yourself when Yahweh your God is driving
        them out before you, saying, \u2018Because of my righteousness Yahweh brought
        me to take possession of this land\u2019; but because of the wickedness of
        these nations Yahweh is driving them out before you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'It is not because of your righteousness and because of the uprightness
        of your heart that you are coming to take possession of their land, but because
        of the wickedness of these nations Yahweh your God is driving them before
        you, and in order to confirm the promise that Yahweh swore to your ancestors,
        to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CSo you should understand that it is not because of your righteousness
        that Yahweh your God is giving you this good land to take possession of it,
        because you are a stubborn people.   "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Remember, do not forget, that you provoked Yahweh your God in the
        desert, and from the day that you went out from the land of Egypt until you
        came to this place you were rebelling against Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAnd remember at Horeb you provoked Yahweh, and Yahweh became
        angry enough to destroy you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When I went up the mountain to receive the stone tablets, the tablets
        of the covenant that Yahweh made with you, and remained on the mountain forty
        days and forty nights, I did not eat food and I did not drink water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Yahweh gave me the two tablets of stone written with the finger
        of God, and on them was writing according to all the words that Yahweh spoke
        with you at the mountain, from the midst of the fire on the day of the assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And then at the end of forty days and forty nights, Yahweh gave me
        the two tablets of stone, the tablets of the covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Yahweh said to me, \u2018Come now, go down quickly from this
        mountain because your people behave corruptly whom you brought out from Egypt,
        for they turned quickly from the way that I commanded them to follow; they
        have made for themselves a cast image.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Yahweh spoke to me, saying, \u2018I have seen this people, and
        look! They are a stubborn people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Leave me alone, and let me destroy them, and let me blot out their
        name from under heaven, and let me make you into a nation mightier and more
        numerous than they!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAnd I turned, and I went down the mountain, as the mountain
        was burning with fire, and the two tablets of the covenant were in my two
        hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And I looked, and indeed you had sinned against Yahweh your God;
        you had made for yourselves an image of a calf of cast metal;  you had turned
        quickly from the way that Yahweh had commanded for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And I took hold of the two tablets, and I threw them out of my two
        hands and smashed them before your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And then I lay prostrate before Yahweh, as earlier, forty days and
        forty nights; I did not eat food and I did not drink water because of all
        your sins that you committed, by doing evil in the eyes of Yahweh and so
        provoking him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For I was in dread from being in the presence of the anger and the
        wrath with which Yahweh was angry with you so as to destroy you, but Yahweh
        listened to me also at that time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And with Aaron Yahweh was angry enough to destroy him, and I prayed
        also for Aaron at that time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And your sinful thing that you had made, the molten calf, I took
        and I burned it with fire, and I crushed it, grinding it thoroughly until
        it was crushed to dust, and I threw its dust into the stream that flowed
        down the mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAnd also at Taberah and at Massah and at Kibroth Hattaavah
        you provoked Yahweh to anger. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And when Yahweh sent you out from Kadesh Barnea, saying, \u2018Go
        up and take possession of the land that I have given you,\u2019 you rebelled
        against the command of Yahweh your God, and you did not believe him, and
        you did not listen to his voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You have been rebellious toward Yahweh from the day I have known
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CAnd I lay prostrate before Yahweh through forty days, and through
        forty nights I prostrated myself, because Yahweh intended to kill you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And I prayed to Yahweh, and I said, \u2018Lord Yahweh, you must not
        destroy your people and your inheritance whom you redeemed in your greatness,
        whom you brought out from Egypt with a strong hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Remember your servants, Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob; you must not pay
        attention to the stubbornness of this people, to their wickedness and to
        their sin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "lest the people of the land from which you brought us out from there
        say, \u201CBecause Yahweh was not able to bring them to the land that he
        promised to them and because of his hatred toward them, he has brought them
        out to kill them in the desert.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "For they are your people and your inheritance whom you brought with
        your great power and with your outstretched arm.\u2019 "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CAt that time Yahweh said to me, \u2018Carve for yourself two
        tablets of stone just as the former ones, and come up the mountain to me,
        and you shall make for yourself an ark of wood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And I will write on the tablets the words that were on the former
        tablets, which you smashed, and you must put them in the ark.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And so I made an ark of acacia wood, and I carved two tablets of
        stone like the former ones, and I went up the mountain with the two tablets
        in my hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he wrote upon the tablets according to the first writing, the
        ten words that Yahweh spoke to you on the mountain from the midst of the
        fire on the day of the assembly, and Yahweh gave them to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I turned, and I came down from the mountain, and I put the tablets
        in the ark that I had made, and they are there, just as Yahweh commanded
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAnd the Israelites journeyed from the wells of Bene-Yaqan to
        Moserah; there Aaron died and was buried, and Eleazar, his son, served as
        a priest in place of him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'From there they journeyed to Gudgodah, and from Gudgodah to Jotbathah,
        a land flowing with streams of water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'At that time Yahweh set apart the tribe of Levi to carry the ark
        of the covenant of Yahweh to stand before Yahweh, to serve him and to bless
        the people in his name until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore there was not for Levi an allotment or an inheritance along
        with his brothers; rather Yahweh is his inheritance just as Yahweh your God
        promised to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And I stayed on the mountain just as during the former forty days
        and forty nights, and Yahweh listened to me also on that occasion; Yahweh
        was not willing to destroy you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Yahweh said to me, \u2018Come, continue your journey before the
        people,  so that you may go and take possession of the land that I swore
        to their ancestors to give to them.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And now, Israel, what is Yahweh your God asking from you, except
        to revere Yahweh your God, to go in all his ways and to love him and to serve
        Yahweh your God with all your heart and with all your soul,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'to keep the commandments of Yahweh and his statutes that I am commanding
        you today for your own good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Look! For to Yahweh your God belong heaven and the highest heavens,
        the earth and all that is in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Yet to your ancestors Yahweh was very attached, so as to love them,
        and so he chose their offspring after them, namely you, from all the peoples,
        as it is today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So you shall circumcise the foreskin of your heart, and do not be
        stubborn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For Yahweh your God, he is God of the gods and Lord of the lords,
        the great and mighty God, the awesome one who is not partial, and he does
        not take bribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he executes justice for the orphan and widow, and he is one who
        loves the alien, to give to them food and clothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And you shall love the alien, for you were aliens in the land of
        Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Yahweh your God, you shall revere him, you shall serve him, and to
        him you shall cling, and by his name you shall swear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He is your praise, and he is your God, who has done with you these
        great and awesome things that your eyes have seen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'With only seventy persons your ancestors went down to Egypt, but
        now Yahweh your God has made you as the stars of the heaven with respect
        to multitude.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CAnd you shall love Yahweh your God, and you shall keep his
        obligations and his statutes and his regulations and his commandments always.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And you shall realize today that it is not with your children who
        have not known and who have not seen the discipline of Yahweh your God\u2014his
        greatness, his strong hand, and his outstretched arm, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and his signs and his deeds that he did in the midst of Egypt to
        Pharaoh, the king of Egypt, and to all of his land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and what he did to the army of Egypt and to their horses and to their
        chariots, and how he made the water of the Red Sea flow over them, when they
        pursued after them, and so Yahweh has destroyed them, as is the case today,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and what he did to you in the desert until you came up to this place, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and what he did to Dathan and to Abiram, the sons of Eliab, the son
        of Reuben, how the earth opened its mouth wide and swallowed them, their
        households and their tents, and all of the living creatures that were in
        their possession and that were following along with them in the midst of
        all of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The fact of the matter is, your own eyes have seen all of the great
        deeds of Yahweh that he did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAnd you must keep all of the commandments that I am commanding
        you today, so that you may have strength and you may go and you may take
        possession of that land to which you are crossing to take possession of it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'so that you may live long on the land that Yahweh swore to your ancestors,
        to give it to them and to their offspring, a land flowing with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the fact is that the land that you are about to go into to take
        possession of it is not like the land of Egypt, from which you have come
        out of, where you sow your seed and you give water by your foot, as in a
        vegetable garden.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the land that you are about to cross into to take possession
        of it is a land of hills and valleys, and by the rain of the heaven it drinks
        water, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'a land that Yahweh your God is caring for it; continually the eyes
        of Yahweh your God are on it, from the beginning of the year up to the end
        of the year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CAnd it will happen that if you listen carefully to my commandments
        that I am commanding you today, to love Yahweh your God, and to serve him
        with all of your heart and with all of your soul,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "then \u2018I will send the rain for your land in its season, early
        rain and later rain, and you will gather your grain and your wine and your
        olive oil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And I will give vegetation in your field for your livestock, and
        you will eat your fill.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Take care so that your heart is not easily deceived, and you turn
        away, and you serve other gods, and you bow down to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And then the anger of Yahweh will be kindled against you, and he
        will shut up the heavens, and there shall not be rain, and so the ground
        will not give its produce, and you will perish quickly from the good land
        that Yahweh is giving to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall put these, my words, on your heart and on your
        inner self, and you shall bind them as a sign on your hand and let them be
        as an emblem between your eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And you shall teach them to your children by talking about them when
        you sit in your house and when you travel on the road and when you lie down
        and when you get up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And you shall write them on the doorframes of your house and on your
        gates, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'so that they may multiply your days and the days of your children
        on the land that Yahweh swore to your ancestors to give it to them as long
        as heaven endures over the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Yes, if you diligently keep all this commandment that I am commanding
        you to observe it,  by loving Yahweh your God by walking in all his ways
        and by holding fast to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'then Yahweh will drive out all of these nations before you, and you
        will dispossess nations larger and more numerous than you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Every place on which the sole of your foot treads, it shall be yours;
        your boundary shall be from the desert and Lebanon from the river, the river
        Euphrates, on up to the western sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'No one can take a stand against you; your dread and your fear Yahweh
        your God will put on the surface of all the land where you tread, just as
        he promised to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CSee, I am setting before you today a blessing and a curse: "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'the blessing, if you listen to the commandments of Yahweh your God
        that I am commanding you today,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and the curse, if you do not listen to the commandments of Yahweh
        your God, but rather you turn from the way that I am commanding you today
        to go after other gods that you have not known. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CAnd it will happen that when Yahweh your God has brought you
        to the land that you are going to, to take possession of it, then you shall
        pronounce the blessing on Mount Gerizim and the curse on Mount Ebal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '(Are they not beyond the Jordan, toward the west, in the land of
        the Canaanites living in the Jordan Valley, opposite Gilgal beside the terebinth
        of Moreh?) '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For you are now about to cross the Jordan to go to take possession
        of the land that Yahweh, your God, is giving to you, and you will take possession
        of it and live in it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "and you must diligently observe all the rules and the regulations
        that I am setting before you today.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Detailed Stipulations: Purity and Unity'
      title: 'Detailed Stipulations: Purity and Unity'
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CThese are the rules and the regulations that you must diligently
        observe in the land that Yahweh, the God of your ancestors, has given to
        you to take possession of it, during all the days that you are living on
        the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You must completely demolish all of the places there where they served
        their gods, that is, the nations whom you are about to dispossess, on the
        high mountains, and on the hills and under each leafy green tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And you shall break down their altars, and you shall smash their
        stone pillars, and their Asherah poles you must burn with fire, and the images
        of their gods you shall hew down, and you shall blot out their names from
        that place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall not worship Yahweh your God like this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But only to the place that Yahweh your God will choose from all of
        your tribes to place his name there as his dwelling shall you seek, and there
        you shall go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And you shall bring there your burnt offerings and your sacrifices
        and your tithes and your donations and your votive gifts and your freewill
        offerings and the firstling of your herd and your flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And you shall eat there before Yahweh your God, and you shall rejoice
        in all your endeavors, you and your family in which Yahweh your God has blessed
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CYou must not do just as we are doing here today, each according
        to all that is right in his eyes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For you have not come up to now to the resting place and to the inheritance
        that Yahweh your God is giving to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But you will cross the Jordan, and you will settle in the land that
        Yahweh your God is giving you as an inheritance, and he will give rest to
        you from all your enemies from all around, and you will live securely, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and then at the place that Yahweh your God will choose, to let his
        name dwell there, there you shall bring all the things I am commanding you,
        your burnt offerings and your sacrifices, your tithes and your donations,
        and all of the choice things, your votive gifts that you vow to Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And you shall rejoice before Yahweh your God, you and your sons and
        your daughters and your slaves and your slave women and the Levite who is
        in your towns, because there is not for him a plot of ground and an inheritance
        with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CTake care for yourself so that you do not offer your burnt
        offerings at just any place that you happen to see, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but only at the place that Yahweh will choose among one of your tribes;
        there you shall offer your burnt offerings, and there you shall do all the
        things that I am commanding you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBut whenever you desire you may slaughter, and you may eat
        meat according to the blessing of Yahweh your God that he has given to you
        in all of your towns; the unclean and the clean may eat it just as they would
        the gazelle and as the deer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Only the blood you must not eat, but on the ground you must pour
        it like water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You are not allowed to eat in your towns the tithe of your grain
        and your wine and your olive oil and the firstborn of your herd and your
        flock and all of your votive gifts that you vowed and your freewill offering
        and your donations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But only before Yahweh your God you shall eat it, at the place that
        Yahweh your God will choose, you and your son and your daughter and your
        slave and your slave woman and the Levite who is in your towns, and you must
        rejoice before your God in all your undertakings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Take care so that you do not neglect the Levite all of your days
        on your land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CWhen Yahweh your God enlarges your territory just as he has
        promised to you, and you say \u2018I want to eat some meat,\u2019 because
        you want it, whenever you desire you may eat meat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'If the place that Yahweh your God will choose to put his name there
        is too far from you, and you slaughter any of your herd and any of your flock
        that Yahweh has given to you just as I have commanded you, then you may eat
        whenever you desire in your towns.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Surely just as the gazelle and the deer is eaten, so both the unclean
        and the clean together may eat it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Only, be sure not to eat the blood, because the blood is the life,
        and you shall not eat the life with the meat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You shall not eat it, but on the ground you shall pour it out like
        water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You shall not eat it, so that it will go well for you and your children
        after you, because then you will be doing what is right in the eyes of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Only your holy objects that are yours and your votive gifts you must
        carry and you must bring to the place that Yahweh will choose. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And you shall offer your burnt offerings, the flesh and the blood
        on the altar of Yahweh your God, and the blood of your sacrifices you shall
        pour out on the altar of Yahweh your God, but the meat you may eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Be careful to obey all these things that I am commanding you, so
        that it will go well for you and for your children after you forever, because
        then you will be doing what is good and right in the eyes of Yahweh your
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CWhen Yahweh your God has cut off the nations whom you are about
        to go to, to dispossess them before you, and you have dispossessed them,
        and you live in their land, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "take care so that you are not ensnared into imitating them after
        their being destroyed from before you, and so that you not enquire concerning
        their gods, saying, \u2018How did these nations serve their gods, and thus
        I myself want to do also.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'You must not do so toward Yahweh your God, because of every detestable
        thing they have done for their gods Yahweh hates, for even their sons and
        their daughters they would burn in the fire to their gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: " All of the things that I am commanding you, you must diligently
        observe; you shall not add to it, and you shall not take away from it.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CIf a prophet stands up in your midst or a dreamer of dreams
        and he gives to you a sign or wonder, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and the sign or the wonder comes about that he spoke to you, saying,
        \u2018Let us go after other gods (those whom you have not known), and let
        us serve them,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'you must not listen to the words of that prophet or to that dreamer,
        for Yahweh your God is testing you to know whether you love Yahweh your God
        with all of your heart and with all of your inner self.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall go after Yahweh your God, and him you shall revere, and
        his commandment you shall keep, and to his voice you shall listen, and him
        you shall serve, and to him you shall hold fast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But that prophet or the dreamer of that dream shall be executed,
        for he spoke falsely about Yahweh your God, the one bringing you out from
        the land of Egypt and the one redeeming you from the house of slavery, in
        order to seduce you from the way that Yahweh your God commanded you to go
        in it; so in this way you shall purge the evil from your midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIf your brother, the son of your mother or your son or your
        daughter or your wife whom you embrace or your intimate friend in secrecy
        says, \u2018Let us go and let us serve other gods!\u2019 gods that you and
        your ancestors have not known, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'from among the gods of the people who are around you, those near
        you or those far from you, from one end of the earth and up to the other
        end of the earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'you must not give in to him, and you shall not listen to him, and
        your eye shall not take pity on him, and you shall not have compassion, and
        you shall not cover up for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But you shall certainly kill him; your hand shall be first against
        him to kill him and next the hand of all of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And you shall stone him with stones and let him die, for he tried
        to seduce you from Yahweh your God, the one bringing you from the land of
        Egypt, from the house of slavery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And all of Israel shall hear, and they shall fear, and they shall
        not continue to act according to this evil thing in your midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIf you hear in one of your towns which Yahweh your God is giving
        to you to live in, someone saying that  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "worthless men have gone out from your midst and have seduced the
        inhabitants of their town, saying, \u2018Let us go and serve other gods!\u2019
        whom you have not known, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'then you shall inquire and examine and interrogate thoroughly, and,
        look! It is true; the thing has actually been done, this detestable thing
        in your midst, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'then you shall certainly strike down the inhabitants of that town
        with the edge of the sword; you shall destroy it and everything in it, its
        domestic animals with the edge of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And then you shall gather all of its booty into the middle of its
        public square, and you shall burn the town and all of its war-booty totally
        for Yahweh your God, and it shall be a pile of rubble forever; it shall not
        be built again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And let not something cling to your hand from the things devoted
        to destruction, so that Yahweh may turn back from his burning anger, and
        he may show compassion to you and he may continue to show compassion and
        so multiply you just as he swore to your ancestors,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "if you listen to the voice of Yahweh your God, to keep all of his
        commandments that I am commanding to you today so as to do the right thing
        in the eyes of Yahweh your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CYou are children of Yahweh your God; therefore you must not
        gash yourself, and you must not make your forehead bald for the dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For you are a people holy to Yahweh your God, and you Yahweh has
        chosen to be a treasured possession from among all of the peoples that are
        on the surface of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall not eat any detestable thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'These are the animals you may eat: ox, sheep, goats,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'deer, gazelle, roebuck, wild goat, ibex, antelope, and mountain sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And any animal having a split hoof and so a dividing of the hoof
        into two parts and that chews the cud among the animals\u2014that animal
        you may eat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Only these you may not eat from those chewing the cud and from those
        having a division of the hoof: the camel and the hare and the coney, because
        they chew the cud, but they do not divide the hoof; they are therefore unclean
        for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And also the pig because it has a division of the hoof but does not
        chew the cud; it is unclean for you; from their meat you shall not eat, and
        you shall not touch their carcasses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThis is what you shall eat from all that is in the water: everything
        that has fins and scales you may eat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But anything that does not have fins and scales, you may not eat,
        for it is unclean for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAll of the birds that are clean you may eat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now these are the ones you shall not eat any of them: the eagle and
        the vulture and the short-toed eagle,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and the red kite and the black kite or any kind of falcon,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and any kind of crow according to its kind, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and the ostrich and the short-eared owl and the seagull and the hawk
        according to its kind, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the little owl and the great owl and the barn owl,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and the desert owl and the carrion vulture and the cormorant,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and the stork and the heron according to its kind and the hoopoe
        and the bat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And also all of the winged insects; they are unclean for you; you
        shall not eat them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You may eat any clean bird. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CYou shall not eat any carcass; you may give it to the alien
        who is in your towns, and he may eat it, or you may sell it to a foreigner,
        for you are a holy people for Yahweh your God; you may not boil a kid in
        its mother\u2019s milk. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CCertainly you must give a tithe of all the yield of your seed,
        which comes forth from your field year after year.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And you shall eat before Yahweh your God in the place that he will
        choose to make to dwell his name there the tithe of your grain, your wine
        and your olive oil and the firstling of your herd and your flock, so that
        you may learn to revere Yahweh your God always.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But if the distance is too great for you, so that you are not able
        to transport it, because the place that Yahweh your God will choose to set
        his name there, it is too far from you, when Yahweh your God will bless you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then in that case you may exchange for money, and you shall take
        the money to your hand and go to the place that Yahweh your God will choose. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You may spend the money for anything that you desire, for oxen or
        for sheep or for wine or for strong drink or for anything that you desire,
        and you shall eat it there before Yahweh your God, and you shall rejoice,
        you and your household. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And as to the Levite who is in your towns, you shall not neglect
        him, because there is not a plot of ground for him and an inheritance along
        with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CAt the end of three years you shall bring out all of the tithe
        of your yield for that year, and you shall store it in your towns.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And so the Levite may come, because there is no plot of ground for
        him or an inheritance with you, and the alien also may come and the orphan
        and the widow that are in your towns, and they may eat their fill, so that
        Yahweh your God may bless you in all of the work of your hand that you undertake.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CAt the end of seven years you shall grant a remission of debt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And this is the manner of the remission of debt: every creditor shall
        remit his claim that he holds against his neighbor, and he shall not exact
        payment from his brother because there a remission of debt has been proclaimed
        unto Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'With respect to the foreigner you may exact payment, but you must
        remit what shall be owed to you with respect to your brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Nevertheless, there shall not be among you a poor person, because
        Yahweh will certainly bless you in the land that Yahweh your God is giving
        to you as an inheritance, to take possession of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If only you listen well to the voice of Yahweh your God by observing
        diligently all of these commandments that I am commanding you today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When Yahweh your God has blessed you, just as he promised to you,
        then you will lend to many nations, but you will not borrow from them, and
        you will rule over many nations, but they will not rule over you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If there is a poor person among you from among one of your brothers
        in one of your towns that Yahweh your God is giving to you, you shall not
        harden your heart, and you shall not shut your hand toward your brother who
        is poor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But you shall certainly open your hand for him, and you shall willingly
        lend to him enough to meet his need, whatever it is.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Take care so that there will not be a thought of wickedness in your
        heart, saying, \u2018The seventh year, the year of the remission of debt
        is near,\u2019 and you view your needy neighbor with hostility, and so you
        do not give to him, and he might cry out against you to Yahweh, and you would
        incur guilt against yourself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'By all means you must give to him, and you must not be discontented
        at your giving to him, because on account of this very thing, Yahweh your
        God will bless you in all your work and in all that you undertake.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For the poor will not cease to be among you in the land; therefore
        I am commanding you, saying, \u2018You shall willingly open your hand to
        your brother, to your needy and to your poor that are in your land.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'If your relative who is a Hebrew man or a Hebrew woman is sold to
        you, and he or she has served you six years, then in the seventh year you
        shall send that person out free.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And when you send him out free from you, you shall not send him away
        empty-handed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall generously supply him from among your flocks and from your
        threshing floor and from your press; according to that with which Yahweh
        your God has blessed you, you shall give to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt, and Yahweh
        your God redeemed you; therefore I am commanding you thus today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And then if it will happen that he says to you, \u2018I do not want
        to go out from you,\u2019 because he loves you and your family, because it
        is good for him to be with you; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'then you shall take an awl, and you shall thrust it through his earlobe
        and into the door, and he shall be to you a slave forever; and you shall
        also do likewise for your slave woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'It shall not be hard in your eyes when you send him forth free, because
        for six years he has served you worth twice the wage of a hired worker; and
        Yahweh your God will bless you in whatever you will do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CEvery firstling male that is born of your herd and of your
        flock you shall consecrate to Yahweh your God; you shall not do work with
        the firstling of your ox, and you shall not shear the firstling of your flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Rather before Yahweh your God you shall eat it year by year at the
        place Yahweh will choose, you and your household. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But if there is a physical defect in it, such as lameness or blindness,
        any serious defect, you shall not sacrifice it to Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In your towns you shall eat it, the unclean and the clean together
        may eat it, just as they eat the gazelle and as they eat the deer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But you shall not eat its blood; you shall pour it on the ground
        like water.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CObserve the month of Abib, and you shall keep the Passover
        to Yahweh your God, for in the month of Abib Yahweh your God brought you
        out from Egypt by night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And you shall offer the Passover sacrifice to Yahweh your God from
        among your flock and herd at the place that Yahweh will choose, to let his
        name dwell there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall not eat with it anything leavened; seven days you shall
        eat with it unleavened bread of affliction, because in haste you went out
        from the land of Egypt, so that you will remember the day of your going out
        from the land of Egypt all the days of your life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And leaven shall not be seen with you in any of your territory for
        seven days, and none of the meat that you will slaughter on the evening on
        the first day shall remain overnight until morning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You are not allowed to offer the Passover sacrifice in one of your
        towns that Yahweh your God is giving to you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'but only at the place that Yahweh your God will choose, to let his
        name dwell there; you shall offer the Passover sacrifice in the evening at
        sunset, at the designated time of your going out from Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And you shall cook, and you shall eat it at the place that Yahweh
        your God will choose; and you may turn in the morning and go to your tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Six days you shall eat unleavened bread, and on the seventh day there
        shall be an assembly for Yahweh your God; you shall not do work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYou shall count off seven weeks for you; from the time you
        begin to harvest the standing grain you shall begin to count seven weeks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And then you shall celebrate the Feast of Weeks for Yahweh your God
        with the measure of the freewill offering of your hand that you shall give
        just as Yahweh your God has blessed you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you shall rejoice before Yahweh your God, you and your son and
        your daughter and your slave and your slave woman and the Levite that is
        in your towns and the alien and the orphan and the widow who are in your
        midst in the place that Yahweh your God will choose to let his name dwell
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And you shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt, and so you
        shall diligently observe these rules. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CYou shall celebrate the Feast of Booths for yourselves seven
        days at the gathering in of the produce from your threshing floor and from
        your press; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and you shall rejoice at your feast, you and your son and your daughter
        and your slave and your slave woman and the Levite and the orphan and the
        widow that are in your towns.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Seven days you shall celebrate your feast to Yahweh your God at the
        place Yahweh will choose, for Yahweh your God shall bless you in all of your
        produce and in all of the work of your hand, and you shall surely be rejoicing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Three times in the year all of your males shall appear before  Yahweh
        your God at the place that he will choose, at the Feast of Unleavened Bread
        and at the Feast of Weeks and at the Feast of Booths, and they shall not
        appear before Yahweh empty-handed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Each person shall give as he is able, that is, according to the blessing
        of Yahweh your God that he has given to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou shall appoint judges and officials for you in all your
        towns that Yahweh your God is giving to you throughout your tribes, and you
        shall render for the people righteous judgments.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You shall not subvert justice; you shall not show partiality; and
        you shall not take a bribe, for the bribe makes blind the eyes of the wise
        and misrepresents the words of the righteous. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Justice, only justice you shall pursue, so that you may live, and
        you shall take possession of the land that Yahweh your God is giving to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You shall not plant for yourselves an Asherah pole beside the altar
        of Yahweh your God that you make for yourselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And you shall not set up for yourselves a stone pillar, a thing that
        Yahweh your God hates. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CYou shall not sacrifice to Yahweh your God an ox or sheep
        that has a physical defect of anything seriously wrong, for that is a detestable
        thing to Yahweh your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'If there is found in one of your towns that Yahweh your God is giving
        to you a man or a woman that does evil in the eyes of Yahweh your God to
        transgress his covenant '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and by going and serving other gods and so he bows down to them and
        to the sun or to the moon or to any of the host of heaven which I have forbidden,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and it is reported to you or you hear about it and you enquire about
        it thoroughly and, indeed, the trustworthiness of the deed has been established,
        it has occurred, this detestable thing, in Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'then you shall bring out that man or that woman who has done this
        evil thing to your gates; that is, the man or the woman, and you shall stone
        them with stones to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'On the evidence of two or three witnesses the person shall be put
        to death. The person shall not be put to death by the mouth of one witness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The hand of the witnesses shall be first against the person to kill
        the person, and afterward the hands of all the people, and so you shall purge
        the evil from your midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CIf a matter is too difficult for you, for example disputes
        between blood and blood, between legal claim and legal claim and between
        assault and assault and between matters of discernment in your towns, then
        you shall get up and you shall go to the place that Yahweh your God will
        choose; "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'then you shall go to the priests and the Levites and to the judge
        who will be in office in those days, and you shall enquire, and they shall
        announce to you the verdict.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall carry out exactly the decision that they announced
        to you from that place that Yahweh will choose, and you shall diligently
        observe according to all that they instruct you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And so according to the instruction of the law that they teach you
        and according to the decisions that they say to you, you shall do; you shall
        not turn from the word that they tell you to the right or to the left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the man who treats with contempt so as not to listen to the priest
        who is standing to minister on behalf of Yahweh your God or to the judge,
        that man shall die; so you shall purge the evil from Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And all the people will hear and will be afraid, and they will not
        behave presumptuously again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CWhen you have come to that land that Yahweh your God is giving
        to you and you have taken possession of it and you have settled in it, and
        you say, \u2018I will set over me a king like all the nations that are around
        me,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'indeed, you may set a king over you whom Yahweh your God will choose,
        from the midst of your countrymen you must set a king over you; you are not
        allowed to appoint over you a man, a foreigner, who is not your countryman.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Except, he may not make numerous for himself horses, and he may not
        allow the people to to go to Egypt in order to increase horses, for Yahweh
        has said to you that you may never return.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he must not acquire many wives for himself, so that his heart
        would turn aside; and he must not accumulate silver and gold for himself
        excessively.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAnd then when he is sitting on the throne of his kingdom, then
        he shall write for himself a copy of this law on a scroll before the Levitical
        priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And it shall be with him, and he shall read it all the days of his
        life, so that he may learn to revere Yahweh your God by diligently observing
        all the word of this law and these rules, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "so as not to exalt his heart above his countrymen and not to turn
        aside from the commandment to the right or to the left, so that he may reign
        long over his kingdom, he and his children in the midst of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CAnd there shall not be for the Levitical priests, the whole
        tribe of Levi, a plot of ground and an inheritance with Israel, rather they
        may eat an offering made by fire as their inheritance, for Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And there shall not be for them an inheritance of land in the midst
        of his brothers; rather Yahweh is his inheritance, just as he promised to
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now this shall be the share of the priest from the people, from those
        who sacrifice the sacrifice, whether it is an ox, sheep, or goat, and they
        shall give the priest the shoulder and the jawbones and the stomach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The firstfruits of your grain, your wine, and your olive oil and
        the firstfruits of the fleece of your sheep you shall give to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For Yahweh your God has chosen him from among all your tribes to
        stand to minister in the name of Yahweh, he and his sons forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And if a Levite comes from one of your towns from anywhere in Israel
        where he is residing, he may come whenever he desires, to the place that
        Yahweh will choose, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and he may minister in the name of Yahweh his God, just like all
        his brothers, the Levites who stand there before Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They shall eat equal portions, apart from what he may receive from
        the sale of his patrimony.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhen you come to the land that Yahweh your God is giving to
        you, you must not learn to do like the detestable practices of those nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'There shall not be found among you one who makes his son or his daughter
        go through the fire, or one who practices divination, or an interpreter of
        signs, or an augur, or sorcerer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'or one who casts magic spells, or one who consults a spirit of the
        dead, or spiritist, or one who inquires of the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For everyone doing these things is detestable to Yahweh, and because
        of these detestable things Yahweh your God is driving them out from before
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You must be blameless before Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For these nations that you are about to dispossess listen to interpreters
        of signs and to diviners, but Yahweh your God has not allowed you to do the
        same. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CYahweh your God will raise up for you a prophet like me from
        your midst, from your countrymen, and to him you shall listen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "This is according to all that you asked from Yahweh your God at Horeb,
        on the day of the assembly, saying, \u2018I do not want again to hear the
        voice of Yahweh my God, and I do not want to see again this great fire, so
        that I may not die!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Yahweh said to me, \u2018They are right in what they have said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will raise up a prophet for them from among their countrymen like
        you, and I will place my words into his mouth, and he shall speak to them
        everything that I command him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And then the man that will not listen to my words that he shall speak
        in my name, I will hold accountable. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "However, the prophet that behaves presumptuously by speaking a word
        in my name that I have not commanded him to speak, and who speaks in the
        name of other gods, then that prophet shall die.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And if you say to yourself, \u2018How can we know the word that Yahweh
        has not spoken to him?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Whenever what the prophet spoke in the name of Yahweh, the thing
        does not take place and does not come about, that is the thing that Yahweh
        has not spoken to him. Presumptuously the prophet spoke it; you shall not
        fear that prophet.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CWhen Yahweh your God has exterminated the nations concerning
        whom Yahweh your God is giving to you their land, and you have dispossessed
        them, and you have settled in their towns and in their houses, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'you shall set apart three cities for you in the midst of your land
        that Yahweh your God is giving to you to take possession of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall prepare the roads for yourselves, and you shall divide
        the regions of your land into thirds that Yahweh your God gives you as a
        possession, so that it will be available for any manslayer to flee there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CNow this is the case of the manslayer who may flee there and
        live there who has killed his neighbor unintentionally, and he did not hate
        him previously.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For example, when somebody goes with his neighbor into the forest
        to cut wood, and the iron head slips from the handle of the tool and strikes
        his neighbor and he dies, then he may flee to one of these cities, and so
        he may live. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He does this lest the avenger of blood might pursue after the killer,
        because he is hot with anger and he overtakes him, because it is a long distance
        to the city of refuge, and so he kills him, but he did not deserve a death
        sentence, because he was not hating him before.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore I am commanding you, saying, \u2018You shall set apart
        three cities.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then if Yahweh your God enlarges your territory just as he swore
        to your ancestors and gives to you all the land that he promised to give
        to your ancestors,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'then if you diligently observe this entire commandment that I am
        commanding you today by loving Yahweh your God and by going in his ways at
        all times, then you shall add three more cities for yourselves to these three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Do this so that innocent blood will not be shed in the midst of your
        land that Yahweh your God is giving to you as an inheritance and thereby
        bloodguilt would be on you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But if someone hates his neighbor and lies in wait for him and rises
        up against him and murders him, and the murderer flees to one of these cities, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then the elders of his city shall send and take him from there, and
        they shall give him into the hand of the avenger of blood, and he shall be
        put to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Your eye shall not take pity on him, and you shall purge the guilt
        of innocent blood from Israel, so that good will be directed toward you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou shall not move the boundary marker of your neighbor that
        former generations set up on your property in the land that Yahweh your God
        is giving to you to take possession of it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The testimony of a single witness may not be used to convict with
        respect to any crime and for any wrongdoing in any offense that a person
        committed; on the evidence of two witnesses or on the evidence of three witnesses
        a charge shall be sustained.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'If a malicious witness gets up to accuse anyone to testify against
        him falsely, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'then the two men to whom the legal dispute pertains shall stand before
        Yahweh, before the priests and the judges who are in office in those days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then judges shall make a thorough inquiry, and if it turns out that
        the witness is a false witness and he testified falsely against his brother, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'then you shall do to him as he meant to do to his brother, and so
        you shall purge the evil from your midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the rest shall hear and shall fear, and they shall not continue
        to do such a thing again as this evil thing in your midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "You must show no pity: life for life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth,
        hand for hand, foot for foot.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CIf you go out to war against your enemies and you see a horse
        and a chariot, an army larger that you, you shall not be afraid because of
        them; for Yahweh your God is with you, the one who brought you from the land
        of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And then when you approach the battle, then the priest shall come
        near and speak to the troops. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he shall say to them, \u2018Hear, Israel, you are near today
        to the battle against your enemies; do not lose heart; you shall not be afraid,
        and you shall not panic, and you shall not be terrified because of them,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "for Yahweh your God is going with you to fight for you against your
        enemies to help you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the officials shall speak to the troops, saying, \u2018Who is
        the man who has built a new house and has not dedicated it? Let him go and
        return to this house, so that he does not die in battle and another man dedicates
        it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And who is the man that has planted a vineyard and has not enjoyed
        it? Let him go and let him return to his house, so that he does not die in
        battle and another man enjoys it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And who is the man who got engaged to a woman and has not married
        her? Let him go and let him return to his house, so that he does not die
        in battle and another man marries her.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the officials shall continue to speak to the troops, and they
        shall say, \u2018What man is afraid and disheartened? Let him go, and let
        him return to his house, and let him not cause the heart of his brothers
        to melt like his.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when the officials have finished speaking to the army troops,
        then they shall appoint commanders of divisions at the head of the troops. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWhen you approach a city to fight against it, you must offer
        it peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And then if they accept your terms of peace and they surrender to
        you, and then all the people inhabiting it shall be forced labor for you,
        and they shall serve you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But if they do not accept your terms of peace and they want to make
        war with you, then you shall lay siege against it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Yahweh your God will give it into your hand, and you shall kill
        all its males with the edge of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Only the women and the little children and the domestic animals and
        all that shall be in the city, all of its spoil you may loot for yourselves,
        and you may enjoy the spoil of your enemies that Yahweh you God has given
        to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Thus you shall do to all the far cities from you, which are not from
        the cities of these nations located nearby.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But from the cities of these peoples that Yahweh your God is giving
        to you as an inheritance, you shall not let anything live that breathes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Rather, you shall utterly destroy them, the Hittites and the Amorites,
        the Canaanites and the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, just as
        Yahweh your God has commanded you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'so that they may not teach you to do like all their detestable things
        that they do for their gods and thereby you sin against Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CIf you besiege a town for many days to make war against it
        in order to seize it, you shall not destroy its trees by wielding an ax against
        them, for you may eat from them, and so you must not cut them down. Are the
        trees of the field humans that they should come in siege against you?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Only the trees that you know are not fruit trees you may destroy
        and you may cut down, and you may build siege works against that city that
        is making war with you until it falls.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CIf someone slain is found in the land that Yahweh your God
        is giving to you to take possession of it and is lying in the field, and
        it is not known who killed him,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'then your elders and your judges shall go out and shall measure the
        distance to the cities that are around the slain one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And then the nearest city to the slain one, the elders of that city
        shall take a heifer of the herd that has not been worked with in the field,
        that has not pulled a yoke, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and the elders of that city shall bring the heifer down to a wadi
        that flows with water all year and that has not been plowed and has not been
        sown; then there they shall break the neck of the heifer in the wadi.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the priests, the descendants of Levi, shall come near, for Yahweh
        your God has chosen them to bless in the name of Yahweh, and every legal
        dispute and every case of assault will be subject to their ruling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And all of the elders of that city nearest to the slain person shall
        wash their hands over the heifer with the broken neck in the wadi.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And they shall declare, and they shall say, \u2018Our hands did not
        shed this blood, and our eyes did not see what was done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Forgive your people, Israel, whom you redeemed, Yahweh, and do not
        allow the guilt of innocent blood in the midst of your people Israel, and
        let them be forgiven with regard to blood.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And so you shall purge the innocent blood from your midst, because
        you must do the right thing in the eyes of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWhen you go out for battle against your enemies, and Yahweh
        your God gives them into your hand, and you lead the captives away, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and you see among the captives a woman beautiful in appearance, and
        you become attached to her and you want to take her as a wife, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then you shall bring her into your household, and she shall shave
        her head, and she shall trim her nails. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And she shall remove the clothing of her captivity from her, and
        she shall remain in your house, and she shall mourn her father and her mother
        a full month, and after this you may have sex with her, and you may marry
        her, and she may become your wife.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And then if you do not take delight in her, then you shall let her
        go to do whatever she wants, but you shall not treat her as a slave, since
        you have dishonored her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CIf a man has two wives, and the one is loved and the other
        one is disliked and the one loved and the one that is disliked have borne
        for him sons, if it happens that the firstborn son belongs to the one that
        is disliked,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'nevertheless it will be the case that on the day of bestowing his
        inheritance upon his sons, he will not be allowed to treat as the firstborn
        son the son of the beloved wife in preference to the son of the disliked
        wife, who is the firstborn son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But he shall acknowledge the firstborn son of the disliked wife by
        giving him a double portion of all that he has, for he is the firstfruit
        of his vigor; to him is the legal claim of the birthright.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIf a man has a stubborn and rebellious son who does not listen
        to the voice of his father and to the voice of his mother, and they discipline
        him, and he does not obey them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'then his father and his mother shall take hold of him, and they shall
        bring him out to the elders of his city and to the gate of his town,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and they shall say to the elders of his city, \u2018This our son
        is stubborn and rebellious; he does not obey us, and he is a glutton and
        a drunkard.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then all the men of his city shall stone him with stones and let
        him die; and so you shall purge the evil from your midst, and all of Israel
        will hear, and they will fear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAnd if a man commits a sin punishable by death, and so he is
        put to death and you hang him on a tree, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "his dead body shall not hang on the tree, but certainly you shall
        bury him on that day, for cursed by God is one that is being hung; so you
        shall not defile your land that Yahweh your God is giving to you as an inheritance.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CYou shall not watch the ox of your neighbor or his sheep or
        goat straying and ignore them; certainly you shall return them to your neighbor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And if your countryman is not near you or you do not know who he
        is, then you shall bring it to your household, and it shall be with you until
        your countryman seeks after it, and you shall return it to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And thus also you shall do regarding his donkey, and thus you shall
        do concerning his garment, and so you shall do with respect to all of the
        lost property of your countryman that is lost from him and you find it; you
        are not allowed to withhold help. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYou shall not see the donkey of your neighbor or his ox fallen
        on the road and you ignore them; certainly you must help them get up along
        with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThe apparel of a man shall not be put on a woman, and a man
        shall not wear the clothing of a woman, because everyone who does these things
        is detestable to Yahweh your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIf a bird\u2019s nest is found before you on the road in any
        tree or on the ground, and there are chicks or eggs, and the mother is lying
        down on the chicks or the eggs, you shall not take the mother along with
        the young; "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'you shall certainly let the mother go, but you may take the young
        for yourselves; do this so that it may go well for you and you may live long
        in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CWhen you build a new house then you shall make a parapet wall
        for your roof, so that you will not bring bloodguilt on your house if anyone
        should fall from it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYou shall not sow your vineyard with differing kinds of seed,
        so that you shall not forfeit the whole harvest, both the seed that you sowed
        and the yield of the vineyard. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou shall not plow with an ox and with a donkey yoked together. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CYou shall not wear woven material made of wool and linen mixed
        together. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CYou shall make tassels for yourselves on the four corners of
        your clothing with which you cover yourself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf a man takes a woman and he has sex with her, but he then
        dislikes her,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and he accuses her falsely, and he defames her, and he says \u2018This
        woman I took and I lay with her and I discovered that she was not a virgin,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'then in defense the father of the young woman shall take, along with
        her mother, and together they must bring out the evidence of the virginity
        of the young woman to display it to the elders of the city at the city gate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And then the father of the young woman shall say to the elders, \u2018I
        gave my daughter to this man as wife, but he now dislikes her, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and now look he has accused her falsely, saying, \u201CI did not
        find your daughter a virgin,\u201D but here is evidence of the virginity
        of my daughter\u2019; and they shall spread the cloth out before the elders
        of the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the elders of that city shall take the man, and they shall discipline
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then they shall fine him a hundred shekels of silver, and they shall
        give them to the father of the young woman, for he defamed an Israelite young
        woman, and she shall become his wife; he will not be allowed to divorce her
        all his days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBut if this charge was true, and the signs of virginity were
        not found for the young woman, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and then they shall bring out the young woman to the doorway of the
        house of her father, and the men of her city shall stone her with stones,
        and she shall die, because she did a disgraceful thing in Israel by playing
        the harlot in the house of her father, and so you shall purge the evil from
        your midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CIf a man is found lying with a married woman, then they shall
        both die; both of them, the man who lay with the woman and the woman also,
        so you shall purge the evil from Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CIf it happens that a young woman, a virgin, is engaged to a
        man, and a man finds her in the town and lies with her, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "then you shall bring out both of them to the gate of that city, and
        you shall stone them with stones so that they shall die, the young woman
        because she did not cry out in the town, and the man because he violated
        his neighbor\u2019s wife; and so you shall purge the evil from your midst. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CBut if the man finds the young engaged woman in the field and
        the man overpowers her and he has sex with her, then the man only must die
        who lay with her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But you shall not do anything to the young woman, for there is not
        reckoned against the young woman a sin deserving death; it is similar to
        when a man rises up against his neighbor and murders him, a fellow human
        being, just so is this case,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'for he found her in the field, the engaged young woman cried out,
        but there was no rescuer to help her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CIf a man finds a young woman, a virgin who is not engaged,
        and he seizes her and he has sex with her and they are caught, "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'then the man who lay with her shall give to the father of the young
        woman fifty shekels of silver, and she shall become his wife because he violated
        her, and he is not allowed to divorce her during his lifetime.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: ' A man may not take the wife of his father, and so he may not dishonor
        his father.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CNo man with crushed testicles or whose male organ is cut off
        may come into the assembly of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'An illegitimate child may not come into the assembly of Yahweh; even
        to the tenth generation none of his descendants may come into the assembly
        of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'An Ammonite or a Moabite may not come into the assembly of Yahweh;
        even to the tenth generation none of his descendants may come into the assembly
        of Yahweh forever,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'because they did not come to meet you with food and with water when
        you came out of Egypt, and also because they hired Balaam, son of Beor, from
        Pethor, in Aram Naharaim to act against you to curse you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But Yahweh your God was not willing to listen to Balaam, and Yahweh
        your God turned the curse into a blessing for you, because Yahweh your God
        loved you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall not promote their welfare or their prosperity all your
        days forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYou shall not abhor an Edomite, because he is your brother;
        you shall not abhor an Egyptian because you were an alien in his land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The children that are born to them in the third generation may come
        representing them in the assembly of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIf you go out to encamp against your enemies, then you shall
        guard against doing anything evil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CIf there is among you a man that is not clean because of a
        seminal emission during the night, he shall go outside the camp; he shall
        not come within the camp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And then toward the coming of the evening, he shall bathe with water,
        and at the going down of the sun, he may come to the midst of the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd there shall be for you a designated place outside the camp;
        and you shall go there to relieve yourself,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and a digging tool shall be included in addition to your other utensils
        for yourself; and then when you relieve yourself outside the camp you shall
        dig with it, and then you shall turn, and you shall cover your excrement. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For Yahweh your God is walking about in the midst of your camp to
        deliver you and to hand your enemies over to you before you, and so let your
        camp be holy, so that he shall not see in it anything indecent, and he shall
        turn away from going with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall not hand over a slave to his master who has escaped
        and fled to you from his master. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He shall reside with you in your midst in the place that he chooses
        in one of your towns wherever he pleases; you shall not oppress him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CNo woman of Israel shall be a temple prostitute, and no man
        of Israel shall be a male shrine prostitute. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You may not bring the hire of a prostitute or the earnings of a male
        prostitute into the house of Yahweh your God, for any vow offerings, because
        both are a detestable thing to Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYou shall not charge your brother interest on money, interest
        on food, or interest on anything that one could lend on interest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You may lend on interest to the foreigner, but to your countryman
        you may not lend on interest, so that Yahweh your God may bless you in all
        your undertakings in the land where you are going, in order to take possession
        of it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CWhen you make a vow to Yahweh your God, you shall not postpone
        fulfillment of it, for certainly Yahweh your God shall require it from you
        and if postponed you will incur guilt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And if you refrain from vowing, you shall not incur guilt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The utterance of your lips you must perform diligently just as you
        have vowed freely to Yahweh your God whatever it was that you promised with
        your mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CWhen you come into the vineyard of your neighbor, then you
        may eat grapes as you please and until you are full, but you shall not put
        any into your container. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CWhen you come into the standing grain of your neighbor, then
        you may pluck ears with your hand, but you may not swing a sickle among the
        standing grain of your neighbor.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CWhen a man takes a wife and he marries her and then she does
        not please him, because he found something objectionable and writes her a
        letter of divorce and puts it in her hand and sends her away from his house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and she goes from his house, and she goes out and becomes a wife
        for another man,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and then the second man dislikes her and he writes her a letter of
        divorce and places it into her hand and sends her from his house, or if the
        second man dies who took her to himself as a wife, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'her first husband who sent her away is not allowed to take her again
        to become a wife to him after she has been defiled, for that is a detestable
        thing before Yahweh, and so you shall not mislead into sin the land that
        Yahweh your God is giving to you as an inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWhen a man takes a new wife he shall not go out with the army,
        and he shall not be obligated with anything; he shall be free from obligation,
        to stay at home for one year, and he shall bring joy to his wife that he
        took. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CA person shall not take a pair of millstones or an upper millstone,
        for he is taking necessities of life as a pledge.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CIf a man is caught kidnapping somebody from among his countrymen,
        the Israelites, and he treats him as a slave or he sells him, then that kidnapper
        shall die, and so you shall purge the evil from among you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Be watchful with respect to an outbreak of any infectious skin disease,
        by being very careful and by acting according to all that the priests and
        the Levites have instructed you, just as I have commanded them, so you shall
        diligently observe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So remember what Yahweh your God did to Miriam on the journey when
        you went out from Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWhen you make a loan to your neighbor, a loan of any kind,
        you shall not go into his house to take his pledge.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You shall wait outside, and the man to whom you are lending, he shall
        bring the pledge outside to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And if he is a needy man, you shall not sleep in his pledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall certainly return the pledge to him as the sun sets, so
        that he may sleep in his cloak and may bless you, and it shall be considered
        righteousness on your behalf before Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou shall not exploit a hired worker, who is needy and poor,
        from among your fellow men or from among your aliens who are in your land
        and in your towns.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'On his day you shall give his wage, and the sun shall not go down,
        because he is poor and his life depends on it; do this so that he does not
        cry out against you to Yahweh, and you incur guilt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CFathers shall not be put to death because of their children,
        and children shall not be put to death because of their fathers; each one
        shall be put to death for his own sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You shall not subvert the rights of an alien or an orphan, and you
        shall not take as pledge the garment of a widow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And you shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt and that Yahweh
        your God redeemed you from there; therefore I am commanding you to do this
        commandment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhen you reap your harvest in your field and you forget a sheaf
        in the field, you shall not return to get it, for it shall be for the alien,
        for the orphan, and for the widow, so that Yahweh your God may bless you
        in all the work of your hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When you beat off the fruit of your olive trees you shall not search
        through the branches afterward, for it shall be for the alien, for the orphan,
        and for the widow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When you harvest grapes, you shall not glean your vineyards again;
        it shall be for the alien, for the orphan, and for the widow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And you shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt,
        therefore I am commanding you to do this thing.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CWhen a legal dispute takes place between men and they come
        near to the court, and the judges judge with respect to them, then they shall
        declare the righteous to be in the right and they shall condemn the wicked, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'then it will happen if the guilty one deserves beating, then the
        judge shall make him lie, and he shall beat him before him, according to
        the prescribed number of lashes proportionate to the offense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He may beat him with forty lashes, and he shall not do more than
        these, so that he will not beat more in addition to these many blows, and
        your countryman would be degraded before your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYou shall not muzzle an ox when he is threshing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWhen brothers dwell together and one of them dies and has no
        son, the wife of the deceased shall not become the wife of a man of another
        family; her brother-in-law shall have sex with her, and he shall take her
        to himself as a wife, and he shall perform his duty as a brother-in-law with
        respect to her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And then the firstborn that she bears shall represent his dead brother,
        so that his name is not blotted out from Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But if the man does not want to take his sister-in-law, then his
        sister-in-law shall go up to the gate, to the elders, and she shall say,
        \u2018My brother-in-law refused to perpetuate his brother\u2019s name in
        Israel, for he is not willing to marry me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the elders of his town shall summon him and speak to him, and
        if he persists and says, \u2018I do not desire to marry her\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "then his sister-in-law shall go near him before the eyes of the elders,
        and she shall pull off his sandal from his foot, and she shall spit in his
        face, and she shall declare and she shall say, \u2018This is how it is done
        to the man who does not build the house of his brother.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And his family shall be called in Israel, \u2018The house where the
        sandal was pulled off.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CIf a man and his brother fight each other and the wife of the
        one man comes near to rescue her husband from the hand of his attacker and
        she stretches out her hand and she seizes his genitals, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then you shall cut off her hand; your eye shall not take pity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThere shall not be for your use in your bag two kinds of stone
        weights, a large one and a small one.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'There shall not be in your house for your use two kinds of measures.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Rather a full and honest weight shall be for your use; there shall
        be for you a full and honest measure, so that your days on the land that
        Yahweh your God is giving to you may be long. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For detestable to Yahweh your God is everyone who is doing such things,
        everyone who is acting dishonestly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CRemember what Amalek did to you on the journey when you went
        out from Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'that he met you on the journey and attacked you, all those lagging
        behind you and when you were weary and worn out, and he did not fear God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And when Yahweh your God gives rest to you from all your enemies
        from around about you in the land that Yahweh your God is giving to you as
        an inheritance to take possession of it, you shall blot out the remembrance
        of Amalek from under the heavens; you shall not forget!\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CAnd then when you come to the land that Yahweh your God is
        giving to you as an inheritance, and you take possession of it and you settle
        in it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'then you shall take from the firstfruit of all the fruit of the ground
        that you harvest from your land that Yahweh your God is giving to you, and
        you shall put it in a basket, and you shall go to the place that Yahweh your
        God will choose to make his name to dwell there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And you shall go to the priest who is in office in those days, and
        you shall say, \u2018I declare today to Yahweh your God that I have come
        into the land that Yahweh swore to our ancestors to give to us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the priest takes the basket from your hand and places it before
        the altar of Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And you shall declare and you shall say before your God, \u2018My
        ancestor was a wandering Aramean, and he went down to Egypt, and there he
        dwelt as an alien few in number, and there he became a great nation, mighty
        and numerous. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the Egyptians treated us badly, and they oppressed us and imposed
        on us hard labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And we cried to Yahweh, the God of our ancestors, and Yahweh heard
        our voice and saw our affliction and our toil and our oppression. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Yahweh brought us out from Egypt with a strong hand and an outstretched
        arm and with great terror and with signs and with wonders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he brought us to this place and gave to us this land, a land
        flowing with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And now, look, I am bringing the firstfruit of the fruit of the ground
        that you gave to me, Yahweh,\u2019 and you shall place it before Yahweh your
        God, and you shall bow down before Yahweh your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you shall celebrate with all of the bounty that Yahweh your God
        gave to you and to your family, you and the Levite and the alien who is in
        your midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhen you are finished giving a tithe, all of the tithe of your
        produce in the third year, the year of the tithe, then you shall give to
        the Levite, to the alien, to the orphan, and to the widow, so that they may
        eat in your towns and they may be satisfied. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And you shall say before Yahweh your God, \u2018I have removed the
        sacred portion from the house and, moreover, I have given it to the Levite
        and to the alien and to the orphan and to the widow according to all your
        commandment that you commanded me; I have not transgressed any of your commandments,
        and I have not forgotten any of them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have not eaten during my time of mourning, and I have not removed
        anything from it while being unclean, and I have not offered any of it to
        someone who has died. I have listened to the voice of Yahweh my God; I have
        done all that you commanded me to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Look down from the dwelling place of your holiness, from heaven,
        and bless your people Israel, and the land that you have given to us, as
        you swore to our ancestors, a land flowing with milk and honey.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThis day Yahweh your God is commanding you to do these rules
        and regulations, and you must observe them diligently with all your heart
        and with all your soul.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Yahweh you have declared today to be for you as your God, and to
        go in his ways and to observe his rules and his commandments and his regulations
        and to listen to his voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Yahweh has declared you today to be for him as a people, a treasured
        possession, as he promised to you, and that you are to observe all his commandments, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and that he then will set you high above all the nations that he
        has made for his praise and for fame and for honor and for you to be a holy
        people to Yahweh your God, as he promised.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ceremonies'
      title: Ceremonies
      number: 1
      content: "Then Moses and the elders of Israel charged the people, saying, \u201CKeep
        all of the commandment that I am commanding you today.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And then on the day that you cross the Jordan to the land that Yahweh
        your God is giving to you, then you shall set up for yourselves large stones,
        and you shall paint them with lime, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and you shall write on them all the words of this law at your crossing,
        so that you may come into the land that Yahweh your God is giving to you,
        a land flowing with milk and honey, as Yahweh, the God of your ancestors,
        promised to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And when you cross the Jordan, you shall set up these stones that
        I am commanding you about today on Mount Ebal, and you shall paint them with
        lime. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And you shall build an altar there for Yahweh your God, an altar
        of stone, but you shall not use an iron tool to shape the stones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You must build the altar of your God with unhewn stones, and you
        shall sacrifice on it burnt offerings to Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And you shall sacrifice fellowship offerings, and you shall eat them
        there, and you shall rejoice before Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You shall write on the stone all of the words of this law very clearly.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Moses and the priests, the Levites, spoke to all Israel, saying,
        \u201CBe silent and hear, Israel, for this day you have become a people for
        Yahweh your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Blessings and Curses'
      title: Blessings and Curses
      number: 10
      content: "And listen to the voice of Yahweh your God, and observe his commandments
        and his rules that I am commanding you today.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Moses charged the people on that day, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThese tribes shall stand on Mount Gerizim to bless the people
        when you cross the Jordan: Simeon and Levi and Judah and Issachar and Joseph
        and Benjamin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And these shall stand on Mount Ebal for delivering the curse: Reuben,
        Gad and Asher and Zebulun, Dan and Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the Levites shall declare, and they shall say to each man of
        Israel with a loud voice, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the man that makes a divine image or a cast image,
        which is a detestable thing for Yahweh, the work of the hand of a skilled
        craftsman, and then sets it in a hiding place.\u2019 And all the people shall
        respond, \u2018Amen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the one who dishonors his father or his mother.\u2019
        And all of the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the one who moves the boundary marker of his neighbor.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the one who misleads a blind person on the road.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the one who deprives the alien, the orphan, and the
        widow of justice.\u2019 And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the one who lies with the wife of his father, because
        he has dishonored his father\u2019s bed.\u2019 And all the people shall say,
        \u2018Amen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the one who lies with any kind of animal.\u2019 And
        all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the one who lies with his sister, the daughter of
        his father or the daughter of his mother.\u2019 And all the people shall
        say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the one who lies with his mother-in-law.\u2019 And
        all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the one who strikes down his neighbor in secret.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the one who takes a bribe to murder an innocent person.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u2018Cursed be the one who does not keep the words of this law,
        to observe them.\u2019 And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CAnd it will happen that if you indeed listen to the voice
        of Yahweh your God, to diligently observe all his commandments that I am
        commanding you today, then Yahweh your God will set you above all the nations
        of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And all of these blessings shall come upon you, and they shall have
        an effect on you if you listen to the voice of Yahweh your God: '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CYou will be blessed in the city, and you will be blessed in
        the field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBlessed will be the fruit of your womb and the fruit of your
        ground and the fruit of your livestock, the calf of your cattle and the lambs
        of your flock.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBlessed will be your basket and your kneading trough. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CBlessed will you be when you come in and blessed will you be
        when you go out.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYahweh will cause your enemies who rise up against you to be
        defeated before you; on one road they shall come out against you, but on
        seven roads they shall flee before you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Yahweh will command concerning you the blessing to be in your barns
        and in all your endeavors; and he will bless you in the land that Yahweh
        your God is giving to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Yahweh will establish you for himself as a holy people as he has
        sworn to you, if you keep the commandments of Yahweh your God and you walk
        in his ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And all of the peoples of the earth shall see that by the name of
        Yahweh you are called, and they shall fear you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Yahweh will make you successful and prosperous, in the fruit
        of your womb and on the land that Yahweh swore to your ancestors to give
        to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Yahweh shall open for you his rich storehouse, even the heavens,
        to give the rain for your land in its time and to bless all of the work of
        your hand, and you will lend to many nations; you will not borrow from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Yahweh shall make you as head and not the tail, and you shall
        be only at the top of the nations, and you shall not be at the bottom, if
        you listen to the commandments of Yahweh your God that I am commanding you
        today and diligently observe them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And you shall not turn aside from any of the words that I am commanding
        you today to the right or left by going after other gods to serve them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAnd then if you do not listen to the voice of Yahweh your God
        by diligently observing all of his commandments and his statutes that I am
        commanding you today, then all of these curses shall come upon you, and they
        shall overtake you: "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CYou shall be cursed in the city, and you shall be cursed in
        the field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYour basket shall be cursed and your kneading trough. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThe fruit of your womb shall be cursed and the fruit of you
        ground, the calves of your cattle and the lambs of your flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYou shall be cursed when you come in, and you shall be cursed
        when you go out.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CYahweh will send upon you the curse, the panic, and the threat
        in everything that you undertake, until you are destroyed and until you perish
        quickly because of the evil of your deeds in that you have forsaken me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Yahweh will cause the plague to cling to you until it consumes you
        from the land that you are going to, to take possession of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Yahweh will afflict you with the wasting diseases and with the fever
        and with the inflammation and with the scorching heat and with the sword
        and with the blight and with the mildew, and they shall pursue you until
        you perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And your heavens that are over your heads shall be like bronze, and
        the earth that is under you shall be like iron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Yahweh will change the rain of your land to fine dust and to sand;
        from the heaven it shall come down upon you until you are destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CYahweh shall cause you to be defeated before your enemies;
        on one road you shall go against them, but you will flee on seven roads before
        them, and you shall become a thing of horror to all of the kingdoms of the
        earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And your dead bodies shall be as food for all of the birds of the
        heaven and to the animals of the earth, and there shall not be anyone to
        frighten them away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CYahweh shall afflict you with the boils of Egypt and with tumors
        and with the scurvy and with the skin rash that cannot be healed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Yahweh shall afflict you with madness and with blindness and with
        confusion of heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And you shall be groping at noon just as the blind person gropes
        in the dark, and you shall not succeed in finding your way, and you shall
        only be abused and robbed all the time, and there will not be anyone who
        will rescue you.   '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'You shall become engaged to a woman, but another man shall sleep
        with her; you shall build a house, but you shall not live in it; a vineyard
        you shall plant, but you shall not enjoy it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Your ox shall be slaughtered before your eyes, and you shall not
        eat it; your donkey shall be stolen right before you, and it shall not be
        returned to you; your sheep and your goats shall be given to your enemies,
        and there shall not be anyone who rescues you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Your sons and your daughters shall be given to other people, and
        you will be looking on longingly for them all day, but you will be powerless
        to do anything.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'A people that you do not know shall consume the harvest of your land
        and all your labor, and you will be only oppressed and crushed for the rest
        of your lives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'You shall become mad because of what your eyes shall see.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Yahweh shall strike you with grievous boils on the knees and on the
        upper thighs from which you will not be able to be healed, from the sole
        of your foot and up to your crown. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Yahweh will bring you and your king whom you set up over you to a
        nation that you or your ancestors have not known, and there you will serve
        other gods of wood and stone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And you will become a horror and a proverb and ridicule among all
        the peoples where Yahweh drives you there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CYou shall carry out much seed to the field, but you shall gather
        little produce, for the locust shall devour it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'You shall plant vineyards and you shall dress them, but you shall
        not drink wine and you shall not gather grapes, for the worm shall eat it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'There shall be olive trees for you in all of your territory, but
        you shall not anoint yourself, for your olives shall drop off. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'You shall bear sons and daughters, but they shall not be yours, for
        they shall go into captivity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The cricket shall take possession of all your trees and the fruit
        of your ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The alien that is in your midst shall ascend over you, higher and
        higher, but you shall go down lower and lower. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'He shall lend to you, but you shall not lend to him; he shall be
        the head, but you shall be the tail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CAnd all of these curses shall come over you, and they shall
        pursue you, and they shall overtake you until you are destroyed, because
        you did not listen to the voice of Yahweh your God, by observing his commandments
        and his statutes that he commanded you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'And they shall be among you as a sign and as a wonder and among your
        offspring forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CBecause of the fact that you did not serve Yahweh your God
        with joy and with gladness of heart for the abundance of everything, "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'then you shall serve your enemies, whom Yahweh will send against
        you under conditions of famine, in thirst, in nakedness, and in a lack of
        everything; and he shall place a yoke of iron on your neck until he has destroyed
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Yahweh will raise up against you a nation from far off, from the
        end of the earth, attacking as the eagle swoops down, a nation whose language
        you will not understand,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'a grim-faced nation who does not show respect to the old and the
        young and does not show pity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'And it shall consume the fruit of your livestock and the fruit of
        your ground until you are destroyed, and who will not leave for you any grain,
        wine, and olive oil, calves of your herds, and lambs of your flock until
        it has destroyed you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'And it shall besiege you in all your towns until your high and fortified
        walls fall, which you are trusting in throughout your land; and it shall
        besiege you in all of your towns in all of your land that Yahweh your God
        has given to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'And you shall eat the fruit of your womb, the flesh of your sons
        and your daughters, whom Yahweh your God gave to you, during the siege and
        during the distress your enemy inflicts upon you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'The most refined and the very sensitive man among you shall be mean
        with his brother and against his beloved wife and against the rest of his
        children that he has left over, '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'by refraining from giving to even one of them any of the meat of
        his children that he eats, because there is not anything that is left over
        for him during the siege and distress that your enemy inflicts upon you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'The most refined and the most delicate woman among you, who shall
        not venture to put the sole of her foot on the ground from being so delicate
        and from such gentleness, shall be mean to her beloved husband and against
        her son and against her daughter, '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'and even concerning her afterbirth that goes out from between her
        feet and also concerning her children that she bears, because she eats them
        for lack of anything in secret during the siege and during the distress that
        your enemy inflicts upon her in your towns.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "\u201CIf you do not diligently observe all the words of this law
        written in this scroll by revering this glorious and awesome name, Yahweh
        your God, "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'then Yahweh shall overwhelm you with your plagues and the plagues
        of your offspring, severe plagues and lasting illnesses, grievous and enduring. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'And he shall bring back upon you all the diseases of Egypt concerning
        which you were in dread because of them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'Also any illness and any plague that is not written in the scroll
        of this law, he shall bring them, Yahweh, upon you until you are destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'And you shall remain only a few people in place of the fact you were
        formerly as the stars of heaven as far as number is concerned, because you
        did not listen to the voice of Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'And then as Yahweh delighted over you to make you prosperous to make
        you numerous, so Yahweh shall delight over you to exterminate you and to
        destroy you, and so you shall be plucked from the land that you are going
        there to take possession of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'And Yahweh shall scatter you among all the nations from one end of
        the earth up to the other end of the earth, and there you shall serve other
        gods that you have not known nor your ancestors, gods of wood and stone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'And among these nations you shall not find rest, and there shall
        not be a resting place for the sole of your foot, and Yahweh shall give you
        there an anxious heart and a weakening of eyes and a languishing of your
        inner self.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'And your life shall hang in doubt before you, and you shall be startled
        night and day, and you shall not be confident of your life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "In the morning you shall say, \u2018If only it was evening!\u2019
        and in the evening you shall say \u2018If only it was morning!\u2019 because
        of the dread of your heart that you shall feel, and because of the sight
        of your eyes that you shall see. "
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: "And Yahweh shall bring you back to Egypt in ships by the route that
        I promised to you that \u2018You shall not see it again!\u2019 And you shall
        sell yourself there to your enemies as slaves and as female slaves, but there
        will not be a buyer.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Covenant Renewal, Oaths, Restoration, Charges to the Nation'
      title: Covenant Renewal, Oaths, Restoration, Charges to the Nation
      number: 1
      content: ' These are the words of the covenant that Yahweh commanded Moses
        to make with the Israelites in the land of Moab besides the covenant that
        he made with them at Horeb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Moses summoned all of Israel and said to them, \u201CYou saw
        all that Yahweh did before your eyes in the land of Egypt and to Pharaoh
        and to all his servants and to all his land; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'that is, the great trials that your eyes saw, and those great signs
        and wonders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Yahweh has not given to you a heart to understand, or eyes to
        see, or ears to hear, even to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I have led you forty years in the desert; your clothes have not
        worn out on you, and your sandal has not worn out on your foot.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You have not eaten bread, and you have not drunk wine and strong
        drink, so that you may know that I am Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when you came to this place then Sihon the king of Heshbon, and
        Og the king of Bashan, came out to meet you for battle, and we defeated them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And we took their land and gave it as an inheritance to the Reubenites
        and to the Gadites and to the half-tribe of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And you must diligently observe the words of this covenant, so that
        you may succeed in all that you do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou are standing today, all of you, before Yahweh your God,
        your leaders, your tribes, your elders, and your officials, all the men of
        Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'your little children, your women and your aliens who are in the midst
        of your camp, from the choppers of your wood to the drawers of your water, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'in order for you to enter into the covenant of Yahweh your God, and
        into his oath that Yahweh your God is making with you today,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'in order to establish you today to himself as a people and so that
        he may be for you as God, just as he promised to you and just as he swore
        to your ancestors, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CNow I am not making this covenant and this oath with you alone.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But with whoever is standing here with us today before Yahweh our
        God, and with whoever is not standing here with us today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For you know how we lived in the land of Egypt and how we traveled
        through the midst of the nations that you traveled through. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And you have seen their detestable things and their idols of wood
        and stone, silver, and gold that were among them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'so that there is not among you a man or a woman or a clan or a tribe
        whose heart turns today from being with Yahweh our God to go to serve the
        gods of these nations, so that there is not among you a root sprouting poison
        and wormwood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And then when he hears the words of this oath, then he will assure
        himself in his heart, saying, \u2018Safety shall be mine even though I go
        in the stubbornness of my heart,\u2019 thereby destroying the well-watered
        land along with the parched.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Yahweh will not be willing to forgive him, for by then the anger
        of Yahweh will smoke, and his passion against that man and all the curses
        written in this scroll will descend on him, and Yahweh will blot out his
        name from under heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Yahweh will single him out for calamity out of all the tribes
        of Israel, according to all the curses of the covenant written in the scroll
        of this law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAnd the next generation, that is, your children who will rise
        up after you, and the foreigner who will come from a distant land, when they
        will see the plagues of that land and its diseases that Yahweh has inflicted
        upon it, will say, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u2018All its land is brimstone and salt left by fire, none of its
        land will be sown, and it will not make plants sprout out and it will not
        grow any vegetation; it is as the destruction of Sodom and Gomorrah, Adman
        and Zeboiim, which Yahweh overturned in his anger and in his wrath.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And all the nations will say, \u2018Why has Yahweh done such a thing
        to this land? What caused the fierceness of this great anger?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And they will say, \u2018It is because they abandoned the covenant
        of Yahweh, the God of their ancestors, which he made with them when he brought
        them out from the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And they went and served other gods and bowed down to them, gods
        whom they did not know them and he had not allotted to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So the anger of Yahweh was kindled against that land to bring upon
        it all the curses written in this scroll, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "and Yahweh uprooted them from their land in anger and in wrath and
        in great fury, and he cast them into another land, just as it is today.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CThe hidden things belong to Yahweh our God, but the revealed
        things belong to us to know and to our children forever, in order to do all
        the words of this law.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CAnd then when all of these things come upon you, the blessing
        and the curse that I have set before you and you call them to mind among
        the nations there where Yahweh your God has scattered you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and you return to Yahweh and you listen to his voice according to
        all that I am commanding you today, both you and your children, with all
        your heart and with all your inner self,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and Yahweh your God will restore your fortunes, and he will have
        compassion upon you, and he will again gather you together from all the peoples
        where Yahweh your God scattered you there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CEven if you are outcasts at the end of the heavens, even from
        there Yahweh your God shall gather you, and from there he shall bring you
        back.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Yahweh your God will bring you to the land that your ancestors
        had taken possession of, and he will make you successful, and he will make
        you more numerous than your ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAnd Yahweh your God will circumcise your heart and the heart
        of your offspring to love Yahweh your God with all your heart and with all
        your inner self so that you may live.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Yahweh your God will put all these curses on your enemies and
        on those who hate you, on those who harassed you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And you will again listen to the voice of Yahweh, and you will do
        all his commandments that I am commanding you today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Yahweh your God will make you prosperous in all your undertakings,
        and in the fruit of your livestock and in the fruit of your ground abundantly,
        for Yahweh will again rejoice over you, just as he rejoiced over your ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He will do this if you listen to the voice of Yahweh your God by
        keeping his commandment and his statutes written in the scroll of this law
        and if you return to Yahweh your God with all your heart and with all your
        inner self.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CFor this commandment that I am commanding you today is not
        too wonderful for you, and it is not too far from you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "It is not in the heavens so that you might say, \u2018Who will go
        up for us to the heavens and get it for us and cause us to hear it, so that
        we may do it?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And it is not beyond the sea, so that you might say, \u2018Who will
        cross for us to the other side of the sea and take it for us and cause us
        to hear it, so that we may do it?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But the word is very near you, even in your mouth and in your heart,
        so that you may do it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CSee, I am setting before you today life and prosperity and
        death and disaster; "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'what I am commanding you today is to love Yahweh your God by going
        in his ways and by keeping his commandments and his statutes and his regulations,
        and then you will live, and you will become numerous, and Yahweh your God
        will bless you in the land where you are going.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'However, if your heart turns aside and you do not listen and you
        are lured away and you bow down to other gods and you serve them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I declare to you today that you will certainly perish; you will not
        extend your time on the land that you are crossing the Jordan to go there
        to take possession of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I invoke as a witness against you today the heaven and the earth:
        life and death I have set before you, blessing and curse. So choose life,
        so that you may live, you and your offspring,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "by loving Yahweh your God by listening to his voice and by clinging
        to him, for he is your life and the length of your days in order for you
        to live on the land that Yahweh swore to your ancestors, to Abraham, to Isaac,
        and to Jacob, to give to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Succession, Deposition, and Recitation of Text'
      title: Succession, Deposition, and Recitation of Text
      number: 1
      content: 'And Moses went and spoke these words to all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CI am a hundred and twenty years old today;
        I am not able to go out and to come in any longer, and Yahweh said to me,
        \u2018You may not cross this Jordan.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Yahweh your God is about to cross before you; he will destroy these
        nations before you, and you shall dispossess them. Joshua will be crossing
        before you, just as Yahweh promised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Yahweh will do to them just as he did to Sihon and to Og, kings
        of the Amorites, and to their land, which he destroyed with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Yahweh will deliver them to you before you, and you shall do
        to them according to every commandment that I have commanded you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Be strong and be courageous; you should not be afraid, and you should
        not be in dread from their presence, for Yahweh your God is the one going
        with you; he will not leave you alone and he will not forsake you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Moses summoned Joshua, and he said to him in the presence of
        all Israel, \u201CBe strong and be courageous, for you will go with this
        people into the land that Yahweh swore to their ancestors to give to them,
        and you will give it to them as an inheritance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Yahweh is the one going before you; he will be with you, and he will
        not leave you alone, and he will not forsake you; you shall not be afraid,
        and you shall not be discouraged.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Moses wrote this law, and he gave it to the priests, the descendants
        of Levi, the ones carrying the ark of the covenant of Yahweh, and to all
        the elders of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Moses commanded them, saying, \u201CAt the end of seven years,
        in the time of the year for canceling debts during the Feast of Booths, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'when all Israel comes to appear before Yahweh their God at the place
        that he will choose, you shall read this law before all Israel in their hearing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Assemble the people, the men and the women and the little children
        and your aliens that are in your towns, so that they may hear and so that
        they may learn and they may revere Yahweh your God, and they shall diligently
        observe all the words of this law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And then their children, who have not known, they too may hear, and
        they may learn to revere Yahweh their God all the days that you live on the
        land that you are crossing the Jordan to get there to take possession of
        it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Yahweh said to Moses, \u201CLook, you are about to die; call
        Joshua and present yourselves in the tent of assembly, so that I may instruct
        him.\u201D So Moses and Joshua went and presented themselves in the tent
        of assembly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Yahweh appeared in the tent in a column of cloud, and the column
        of the cloud stood at the entrance of the tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Yahweh said to Moses, \u201CLook, you are about to lie down with
        your ancestors, and this people will arise and they will play the prostitute
        after the foreign gods of the land to which they are going.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And my anger shall flare up against them on that day, and I will
        forsake them, and I will hide my face from them, and they shall become as
        prey, and disasters and troubles shall find them, and they shall say on that
        day, \u2018Is it not because our God is not in our midst that these disasters
        have found us?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But I will certainly hide my face on that day, because of all of
        the evil that they did because they turned to other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CAnd so then write this song for yourselves and teach it to
        the Israelites; put it in their mouth, so that this song may be for me as
        a witness against the Israelites.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For when I bring them into the land that I swore to their ancestors,
        a land flowing with milk and honey, they will eat their fill, and they will
        become fat, and then they will turn to other gods, and they will serve them,
        and they will spurn me, and they will break my covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And then many disasters and troubles will come upon them, and this
        song will give evidence before them as a witness, because it will not be
        forgotten from out of the mouth of their descendants, for I know their inclination
        that they are having today before I have brought them into the land that
        I swore.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Moses wrote this song on that day and taught it to the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then he told Joshua the son of Nun, and said to him, \u201CBe strong
        and be courageous, for you shall bring the Israelites into the land that
        I swore to them, and I will be with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And then when Moses finished writing the words of this law on the
        scroll until they were complete,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then Moses commanded the Levites carrying the ark of the covenant
        of Yahweh, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CTake the scroll of this law and put it at the side of the ark
        of the covenant of Yahweh your God, and it will be there as a witness against
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For I know your rebellion and your stiff neck even now while I am
        still alive with you today, rebelling against Yahweh, and how much more after
        my death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Assemble to me all the elders of your tribes and your officials,
        so that I may speak in their ears these words, and that I may call as witness
        against them heaven and earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "For I know that after my death you will certainly act corruptly,
        and you will turn aside from the way that I have commanded you, and the disaster
        in the future days will befall you, because you will do evil in the eyes
        of Yahweh, provoking him with the work of your hands.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So Moses spoke into the ears of the assembly of Israel the words
        of this song until they were complete.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Song of Moses'
      title: The Song of Moses
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CGive ear, O heavens, and I will speak, and let the earth hear
        the words of my mouth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'May my teaching trickle like the dew, my words like rain showers
        on tender grass, and like spring showers on new growth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I will proclaim the name of Yahweh; ascribe greatness to our
        God! '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Rock, his work is perfect, for all his ways are just; he is a
        faithful God, and without injustice;  righteous and upright is he. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They have behaved corruptly toward him; they are not his children;
        this is their flaw, a generation crooked and perverse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Like this do you treat Yahweh, foolish and unwise people? Has he
        not, your father, created you? He made you, and he established you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Remember the old days, the years long past;  ask your father, and
        he will inform you, your elders and they will tell you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When the Most High apportioned the nations, at his dividing up of
        the sons of humankind, he fixed the boundaries of the peoples, according
        to the number of the children of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For Yahweh\u2019s portion was his people, Jacob the share of his
        inheritance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He found him in a desert land, and in a howling, desert wasteland;
        he encircled him, he cared for him, he protected him like the apple of his
        eye. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As an eagle stirs up its nest, hovers over its young, spreads out
        its wings, takes them,  carries them on its pinions,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'so Yahweh alone guided him,  and there was no foreign god accompanying
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he set him on the high places of the land, and he fed him the
        crops of the field, and he nursed him with honey from crags,  and with oil
        from flinty rock, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'With curds from the herd, and with milk from the flock, with the
        fat of young rams, and rams, the offspring of Bashan, and with goats along
        with the finest kernels of wheat, and from the blood of grapes you drank
        fermented wine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Jeshurun grew fat, and he kicked; you grew fat, you bloated,
        and you became obstinate; and he abandoned God, his maker, and he scoffed
        at the rock of his salvation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They made him jealous with strange gods; with detestable things they
        provoked him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They sacrificed to the demons, not God, to gods whom they had not
        known, new gods who came from recent times; their ancestors had not known
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The rock who bore you, you neglected, and you forgot God, the one
        giving you birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Yahweh saw, and he spurned them, because of the provocation
        of his sons and his daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So he said, \u2018I will hide my face from them; I will see what
        will be their end, for they are a generation of perversity, children in whom
        there is no faithfulness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They annoyed me with what is not a god; they provoked me with their
        idols. So I will make them jealous with those not a people, with a foolish
        nation I will provoke them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For a fire was kindled by my anger, and it burned up to the depths
        of Sheol,  and it devoured the earth and its produce, and it set afire the
        foundation of the mountains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I will heap disasters upon them; my arrows I will spend on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They will become weakened by famine, and consumed by plague and bitter
        pestilence; and the teeth of wild animals I will send against them, with
        the poison of the creeping things in the dust; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'From outside her boundaries the sword will make her childless, and
        from inside, terror; both for the young man and also the young woman, the
        infant along with the gray-headed man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I thought, \u201CI will wipe them out; I will make people forget
        they ever existed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "If I had not feared a provocation of the enemy, lest their foes might
        misunderstand,   lest they should say,  \u201COur hand is triumphant, and
        Yahweh did not do all this.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For they are a nation void of sense,  and there is not any understanding
        in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'If only they were wise, they would understand this; they would discern
        for themselves their end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'How could one chase a thousand and two could cause a myriad to flee,
        if their Rock had not sold them, and Yahweh had not given them up? '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For the fact of the matter is, their rock is not like our Rock, and
        our enemies recognize this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For their vine is from the vine of Sodom, and from the terraces of
        Gomorrah; their grapes are grapes of poison; their clusters are bitter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Their wine is the poison of snakes, and the deadly poison of horned
        vipers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u2018Is not this stored up with me, sealed in my treasuries?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Vengeance belongs to me and also recompense, for at the time their
        foot slips,  because the day of their disaster is near, and fate comes quickly
        for them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For Yahweh will judge on behalf of his people, and concerning his
        servants; he will change his mind when he sees that their power has disappeared,
        and there is no one left, confined or free.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And he will say, \u2018Where are their gods, their rock in whom they
        took refuge? "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Who ate the fat of their sacrifices and drank the wine of their libations?
        Let them rise up, and let them help you; Let them be to you a refuge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'See, now, that I, even I am he, and there is not a god besides me;
        I put to death and I give life; I wound and I heal; there is not one who
        delivers from my hand! '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'For indeed I lift up my hand to heaven, And I promise as I live forever,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'When I sharpen my flashing sword,  and my hand takes hold of it in
        judgment, I will take reprisals against my foes,  and my haters I will repay. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "I will make my arrows drunk with blood, and my sword shall devour
        flesh with the blood of the slain, and captives from the heads of the leaders
        of the enemy.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Call for songs of joy, O nations, concerning his people,  for the
        blood of his servants he will avenge, and he will take reprisals against
        his foes,  and he will make atonement for his land, his people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And Moses came, and he spoke all the words of this song in the ears
        of the people; that is, he and Joshua the son of Nun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And when Moses finished speaking all these words to all Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "then he said to them, \u201CTake to heart all the words that I am
        admonishing against you today concerning which you should instruct them with
        respect to your children so that they will observe diligently all the words
        of this law, "
      comments: []
    - name: "47: Instructions Concerning Moses\u2019 Death"
      title: "Instructions Concerning Moses\u2019 Death"
      number: 47
      content: "for it is not a trifling matter among you, but it is your life, and
        through this word you will live long in the land that you are about to cross
        the Jordan to get there to take possession of it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And Yahweh said to Moses on exactly this day, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "\u201CGo up to this mountain of the Abarim range, Mount Nebo, which
        is opposite Jericho, and see the land of Canaan that I am giving to the Israelites
        as a possession. "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'You shall die on that mountain that you are about to go up there,
        and you will be gathered to your people, just as your brother Aaron died
        on Mount Hor and he was gathered to his people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'because of the fact that you broke faith with me in the midst of
        Israel at the waters of Meribah Kadesh, in the desert of Zin, because you
        did not treat me as holy in the midst of the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "Yes, from afar you may view the land, but there you shall not enter
        there, that is, into the land that I am giving to the Israelites.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Blessings of Moses on Israel'
      title: Blessings of Moses on Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'Now this is the blessing with which Moses, the man of God, blessed
        the Israelites before his death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then he said, \u201CYahweh came from Sinai, and he dawned upon them
        from Seir; he shone forth from Mount Paran, and he came with myriads of holy
        ones, at his right hand a fiery law for them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Moreover, he loves his people,  all the holy ones were in your hand,
        and they bowed down to your feet, each one accepted directions from you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'A law Moses instructed for us, as a possession for the assembly of
        Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And then a king arose in Jeshurun, at the gathering of the leaders
        of the people, united were the tribes of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CMay Reuben live, and may he not die, and let his number not
        be few.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he said this of Judah,  \u201CHear, O Yahweh, the voice of Judah,
        and bring him to his people; his own hands strive for him, and may you be
        a help against his foes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And of Levi he said, \u201CYour Thummim and your Urim are for your
        faithful one,  whom you tested at Massah;  you contended with him at the
        waters of Meribah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The one saying of his father and of his mother, \u2018I have not
        regarded them,\u2019 and his brothers he did not acknowledge, and his children
        he did not know, but rather they observed your word, and your covenant they
        kept. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They taught your regulations to Jacob, and your law to Israel; they
        placed incense smoke before you,  and whole burnt offerings on your altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Bless, O Yahweh, his substance, and with the work of his hands you
        must be pleased; smite the loins of those who attack him, and those hating
        him, so that they cannot arise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Of Benjamin he said, \u201CThe beloved of Yahweh dwells securely, 
        the Most High shields all around him, all the day, and between his shoulders
        he dwells.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And of Joseph he said, \u201CBlessed by Yahweh is his land, with
        the choice things of heaven, with dew, and with the deep lying down beneath, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and with the choice things of the fruits of the the sun, and with
        the choice things of the yield of the seasons,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and with the finest things of the ancient mountains, and with the
        choice things of the eternal hills,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and with the choice things of the earth and its fullness, and the
        favor of the one who dwelt in the bush.  Let them come to the head of Joseph,
        and to the crown of the prince among his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "As the firstborn of his ox, majesty belongs to him,  and his horns
        are the horns of a wild ox; with them he drives people together,  and they
        are the myriads of Ephraim, and they are the thousands of Manasseh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And of Zebulun he said, \u201CRejoice, Zebulun, in your going out,
        and rejoice, Issachar, in your tents; "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They summon people to the mountains;  there they sacrifice the sacrifices
        of righteousness, because the affluence of the seas they suck out, and the
        most hidden treasures of the sand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And of Gad he said, \u201CBlessed be the one who enlarges Gad;  like
        a lion he dwells, and he tears an arm as well as a scalp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he selected the best part for himself,   for there the portion
        of a ruler is included, and he came with the heads of the people;  he did
        the righteousness of Yahweh, and his regulations for Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And of Dan he said, \u201CDan is a cub of a lion; he leaps from Bashan.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And of Naphtali, he said, \u201COh, Naphtali, sated of favor, and
        full of the blessing of Yahweh; take possession of the lake, and the land
        to the south.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And of Asher he said, \u201CBlessed more than sons is Asher; may
        he be the favorite of his brothers, dipping his feet in the oil.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Your bars are iron and bronze, and as your days, so is your strength.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThere is no one like God, O, Jeshurun, who rides through the
        heavens to your help, and with his majesty through the skies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The God of ancient time is a hiding place, and underneath are the
        arms of eternity,  and he drove out from before you your enemy, and he said,
        \u2018Destroy them!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Israel dwells alone and carefree, the spring of Jacob in a land
        of grain and wine; his heavens even drip dew. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Blessed are you, O Israel. Who is like you, a people who is saved
        by Yahweh, the shield of your help, and who is the sword of your triumph,
        and your enemies, they shall fawn before you,  and you shall tread on their
        backs.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death of Moses and the Commissioning of Joshua'
      title: The Death of Moses and the Commissioning of Joshua
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Moses went up from the desert plateau of Moab to Mount Nebo,
        to the top of Pisgah, which is opposite Jericho, and Yahweh showed him all
        of the land, Gilead all the way up to Dan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and all of Naphtali and the land of Ephraim and Manasseh and all
        of the land of Judah, up to the western sea,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the Negev and the plain of the valley of Jericho, the city of
        palms, on up to Zoar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Yahweh said to him, \u201CThis is the land that I swore to Abraham
        to Isaac and to Jacob, saying, \u2018To your offspring I will give it.\u2019
        I have let you see it with your eyes, but you shall not cross into it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Moses, the servant of Yahweh, died there in the land of Moab
        according to the command of Yahweh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he buried him in the valley in the land of Moab opposite Beth
        Peor. But until this day no one knows his burial site. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now Moses was a hundred and twenty years old when he died; his sight
        was not impaired and his vigor had not abated.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the Israelites wept concerning Moses thirty days; finally the
        days of weeping and mourning for Moses were completed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now Joshua the son of Nun was full of the spirit of wisdom because
        Moses had placed his hands on him, and the Israelites listened to him, and
        they did as Yahweh had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And not again has a prophet arisen in Israel like Moses, whom Yahweh
        knew face to face, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'as far as all the signs and the wonders Yahweh sent him to do in
        the land of Egypt, against Pharaoh and all of his servants and against all
        of his land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and as far as all of the mighty deeds and as far as the great awesome
        wonders Moses did before the eyes of all Israel. '
      comments: []
